('General Education','Science','medium','Which state of matter has a definite shape and volume?','[{"key": "A", "text": "Gas"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Liquid"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Plasma"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Solid"}]','D','The correct answer is D. Solid.','elementary'),
('General Education','Science','medium','Newton''s First Law of Motion states that:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Force equals mass times acceleration"}, {"key": "B", "text": "An object in motion stays in motion unless acted upon by an external force"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Every action has an equal and opposite reaction"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Gravity pulls objects toward Earth"}]','B','The correct answer is B. An object in motion stays in motion unless acted upon by an external force.','elementary'),
