('General Education','Social Studies','medium','The largest island in the Philippines is:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Mindanao"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Palawan"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Luzon"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Samar"}]','C','The correct answer is C. Luzon.','elementary'),
('General Education','Social Studies','medium','''Pakikisama'' in Filipino culture means:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Competition"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Group harmony and getting along with others"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Individual achievement"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Avoiding conflict through silence"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Group harmony and getting along with others.','elementary'),
('General Education','Social Studies','medium','The French Revolution began in:','[{"key": "A", "text": "1776"}, {"key": "B", "text": "1789"}, {"key": "C", "text": "1800"}, {"key": "D", "text": "1815"}]','B','The correct answer is B. 1789.','elementary'),
('General Education','Social Studies','medium','The three branches of the Philippine government are:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Executive, Military, Judiciary"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Legislative, Executive, Judicial"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Senate, House, President"}, {"key": "D", "text": "National, Regional, Local"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Legislative, Executive, Judicial.','elementary'),
('General Education','Social Studies','medium','Supply and demand is a concept in:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Political science"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Sociology"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Economics"}, {"key": "D", "text": "History"}]','C','The correct answer is C. Economics.','elementary'),
('General Education','Social Studies','medium','The right to free speech is guaranteed under the Philippine:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Civil Code"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Constitution"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Labor Code"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Family Code"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Constitution.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','Child and Adolescent Development','medium','According to Piaget, a child who can sort objects by color and size is in the ___ stage:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Sensorimotor"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Preoperational"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Concrete Operational"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Formal Operational"}]','C','The correct answer is C. Concrete Operational.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','Child and Adolescent Development','medium','Vygotsky believed that learning is primarily a ___ process:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Individual cognitive"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Social and cultural"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Biological maturation"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Behavioral conditioning"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Social and cultural.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','Child and Adolescent Development','medium','In Bloom''s revised taxonomy, ''Evaluating'' is at which level (1=lowest, 6=highest)?','[{"key": "A", "text": "Level 3"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Level 4"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Level 5"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Level 6"}]','C','The correct answer is C. Level 5.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','Child and Adolescent Development','medium','Maslow''s most basic (physiological) needs include:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Love and belonging"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Self-esteem"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Food, water, shelter"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Safety"}]','C','The correct answer is C. Food, water, shelter.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','Child and Adolescent Development','medium','Social Learning Theory by Bandura emphasizes ___ as key to learning:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Punishment"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Observation and modeling"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Reinforcement schedules"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Cognitive schemas"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Observation and modeling.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','Child and Adolescent Development','medium','Jerome Bruner''s Spiral Curriculum means:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Teaching in circles"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Revisiting topics with increasing depth as students develop"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Teaching all topics once only"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Focusing on one subject at a time"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Revisiting topics with increasing depth as students develop.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','Child and Adolescent Development','medium','Thorndike''s Law of Effect states that:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Learning occurs through observation"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Behavior followed by satisfying consequences tends to be repeated"}, {"key": "C", "text": "All behavior is innate"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Learning requires social interaction"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Behavior followed by satisfying consequences tends to be repeated.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','Principles of Teaching','medium','The first step in making a lesson plan is to:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Prepare materials"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Define learning objectives"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Write the assessment"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Choose teaching strategies"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Define learning objectives.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','Principles of Teaching','medium','Problem-based learning encourages students to:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Memorize facts"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Solve real-world problems through inquiry"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Copy from textbooks"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Listen to lectures only"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Solve real-world problems through inquiry.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','Principles of Teaching','medium','Summative assessment is BEST described as:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Assessment during learning"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Assessment of learning (at the end of a unit)"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Self-assessment by students"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Peer assessment"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Assessment of learning (at the end of a unit).','elementary'),
('Professional Education','Principles of Teaching','hard','The MOST effective way to teach a heterogeneous class is:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Teach only to average students"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Focus on advanced students"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Use differentiated instruction"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Give the same worksheet to all"}]','C','The correct answer is C. Use differentiated instruction.','elementary'),
