('General Education','Social Studies','medium','The Senate of the Philippines is composed of how many senators?','[{"key": "A", "text": "24"}, {"key": "B", "text": "300"}, {"key": "C", "text": "12"}, {"key": "D", "text": "50"}]','A','The correct answer is A. 24.','elementary'),
('General Education','Social Studies','medium','Gross Domestic Product (GDP) measures:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Total imports and exports"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Total value of goods and services produced in a country"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Government spending only"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Population growth"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Total value of goods and services produced in a country.','elementary'),
('General Education','Social Studies','medium','ASEAN stands for:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Asian State Economic Agreement Network"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Association of Southeast Asian Nations"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Asian Social and Economic Alliance Network"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Alliance of Southeast Asian Nations"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Association of Southeast Asian Nations.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','Child and Adolescent Development','medium','According to Piaget, a child using symbolic thinking (pretend play) is in the:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Sensorimotor stage"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Preoperational stage"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Concrete Operational stage"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Formal Operational stage"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Preoperational stage.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','Child and Adolescent Development','medium','The concept of ''More Knowledgeable Other'' (MKO) is part of:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Piaget''s theory"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Vygotsky''s sociocultural theory"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Maslow''s hierarchy"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Bloom''s taxonomy"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Vygotsky''s sociocultural theory.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','Child and Adolescent Development','medium','''Application'' in Bloom''s Taxonomy involves:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Memorizing facts"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Understanding concepts"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Using knowledge in new situations"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Breaking information into parts"}]','C','The correct answer is C. Using knowledge in new situations.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','Child and Adolescent Development','medium','Which Maslow need must be met BEFORE pursuing self-esteem needs?','[{"key": "A", "text": "Self-actualization"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Love and belonging"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Safety"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Cognitive needs"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Love and belonging.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','Child and Adolescent Development','medium','An example of negative reinforcement is:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Giving a student a prize for good behavior"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Removing a homework task when a student performs well"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Punishing a student for misbehavior"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Ignoring bad behavior"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Removing a homework task when a student performs well.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','Child and Adolescent Development','medium','Discovery learning is associated with:','[{"key": "A", "text": "B.F. Skinner"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Jerome Bruner"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Jean Piaget"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Albert Bandura"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Jerome Bruner.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','Child and Adolescent Development','medium','Thorndike''s Law of Readiness states that:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Practice makes learning permanent"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Learning is more effective when the learner is ready"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Rewards strengthen behavior"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Observation leads to learning"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Learning is more effective when the learner is ready.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','Principles of Teaching','medium','An objective starting with ''The student will be able to IDENTIFY...'' belongs to which domain?','[{"key": "A", "text": "Psychomotor"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Affective"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Cognitive"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Social"}]','C','The correct answer is C. Cognitive.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','Principles of Teaching','medium','Think-Pair-Share is an example of:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Individual seat work"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Cooperative learning strategy"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Rote memorization"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Direct instruction"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Cooperative learning strategy.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','Principles of Teaching','medium','Portfolio assessment is BEST used to:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Rank students in class"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Show student growth and progress over time"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Compare students to national standards"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Test memorization"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Show student growth and progress over time.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','Principles of Teaching','hard','Which curriculum approach connects different subjects around a common theme?','[{"key": "A", "text": "Subject-centered"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Integrated/Thematic curriculum"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Core curriculum"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Activity curriculum"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Integrated/Thematic curriculum.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','Principles of Teaching','hard','''With-it-ness'' in classroom management refers to a teacher''s ability to:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Know all subjects"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Be aware of what is happening in the classroom at all times"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Control students with fear"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Teach without preparation"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Be aware of what is happening in the classroom at all times.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','Principles of Teaching','hard','Which is NOT a principle of effective instructional materials?','[{"key": "A", "text": "Appropriateness to learner level"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Accuracy of content"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Aesthetic quality"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Expensive production cost"}]','D','The correct answer is D. Expensive production cost.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','Principles of Teaching','hard','The 5E model of instruction stands for:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Engage, Explore, Explain, Elaborate, Evaluate"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Enable, Examine, Experience, Extend, Evaluate"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Educate, Explore, Explain, Expand, Examine"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Engage, Examine, Execute, Elaborate, Evaluate"}]','A','The correct answer is A. Engage, Explore, Explain, Elaborate, Evaluate.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','The Teaching Profession','hard','A teacher who shows favoritism in grading violates the principle of:','[{"key": "A", "text": "School policy"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Fairness and impartiality"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Academic freedom"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Curriculum standards"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Fairness and impartiality.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','The Teaching Profession','hard','The PRC (Professional Regulation Commission) was established under:','[{"key": "A", "text": "RA 8981"}, {"key": "B", "text": "RA 7836"}, {"key": "C", "text": "RA 4670"}, {"key": "D", "text": "RA 9155"}]','A','The correct answer is A. RA 8981.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','The Teaching Profession','hard','Which law mandates that teachers cannot be dismissed without just cause?','[{"key": "A", "text": "RA 7836"}, {"key": "B", "text": "RA 4670 \u2014 Magna Carta for Teachers"}, {"key": "C", "text": "RA 9155"}, {"key": "D", "text": "RA 6713"}]','B','The correct answer is B. RA 4670 — Magna Carta for Teachers.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','The Teaching Profession','hard','A teacher who maintains confidentiality of students'' records is practicing:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Transparency"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Professional ethics and privacy protection"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Excessive secrecy"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Administrative compliance"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Professional ethics and privacy protection.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','The Teaching Profession','hard','The Philippine National Anthem was composed by (lyrics / music):','[{"key": "A", "text": "Jose Palma (lyrics) and Julian Felipe (music)"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Jose Rizal"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Andres Bonifacio"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Nick Joaquin"}]','A','The correct answer is A. Jose Palma (lyrics) and Julian Felipe (music).','elementary'),
('Professional Education','The Teaching Profession','hard','The right of teachers to organize unions is protected by:','[{"key": "A", "text": "The Bill of Rights in the Constitution"}, {"key": "B", "text": "RA 7836"}, {"key": "C", "text": "School policy"}, {"key": "D", "text": "DepEd regulations"}]','A','The correct answer is A. The Bill of Rights in the Constitution.','elementary'),
('General Education','English','easy','Which sentence uses a semicolon correctly?','[{"key": "A", "text": "I love reading; but I hate math."}, {"key": "B", "text": "She studied hard; therefore, she passed the exam."}, {"key": "C", "text": "He ran; fast."}, {"key": "D", "text": "They ate; and slept."}]','B','The correct answer is B. She studied hard; therefore, she passed the exam..','elementary'),
('General Education','English','easy','What is the past tense of ''begin''?','[{"key": "A", "text": "Began"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Begined"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Begun"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Beginned"}]','A','The correct answer is A. Began.','elementary'),
('General Education','English','easy','A word that sounds like its meaning (e.g., ''buzz'', ''crash'') is called:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Metaphor"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Onomatopoeia"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Alliteration"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Irony"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Onomatopoeia.','elementary'),
('General Education','English','easy','The suffix ''-ful'' in ''beautiful'' means:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Without"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Full of or having the quality of"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Against"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Before"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Full of or having the quality of.','elementary'),
('General Education','English','easy','Which is a proper noun?','[{"key": "A", "text": "city"}, {"key": "B", "text": "teacher"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Manila"}, {"key": "D", "text": "mountain"}]','C','The correct answer is C. Manila.','elementary'),
('General Education','English','easy','''The assignment was finished by the students'' is in ___ voice:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Active"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Future"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Passive"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Progressive"}]','C','The correct answer is C. Passive.','elementary'),
('General Education','English','easy','An autobiography is a book written about:','[{"key": "A", "text": "A famous person by another author"}, {"key": "B", "text": "The author''s own life"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Historical events"}, {"key": "D", "text": "A fictional character"}]','B','The correct answer is B. The author''s own life.','elementary'),
('General Education','English','easy','Which sentence uses ''affect'' correctly?','[{"key": "A", "text": "The rain will effect our plans."}, {"key": "B", "text": "The rain will affect our plans."}, {"key": "C", "text": "The medicine had a good affect."}, {"key": "D", "text": "The affect of the storm was severe."}]','B','The correct answer is B. The rain will affect our plans..','elementary'),
('General Education','Mathematics','medium','What is the next number in the pattern: 2, 4, 8, 16, ___?','[{"key": "A", "text": "18"}, {"key": "B", "text": "24"}, {"key": "C", "text": "32"}, {"key": "D", "text": "64"}]','C','The correct answer is C. 32.','elementary'),
('General Education','Mathematics','medium','Convert 3/8 to a decimal:','[{"key": "A", "text": "0.35"}, {"key": "B", "text": "0.375"}, {"key": "C", "text": "0.38"}, {"key": "D", "text": "0.3"}]','B','The correct answer is B. 0.375.','elementary'),
('General Education','Mathematics','medium','The circumference of a circle with radius 7 cm (use π ≈ 22/7) is:','[{"key": "A", "text": "22 cm"}, {"key": "B", "text": "44 cm"}, {"key": "C", "text": "154 cm"}, {"key": "D", "text": "49 cm"}]','B','The correct answer is B. 44 cm.','elementary'),
('General Education','Mathematics','medium','A bus travels 240 km in 4 hours. What is its average speed?','[{"key": "A", "text": "40 km/h"}, {"key": "B", "text": "50 km/h"}, {"key": "C", "text": "60 km/h"}, {"key": "D", "text": "80 km/h"}]','C','The correct answer is C. 60 km/h.','elementary'),
('General Education','Mathematics','medium','What is 4² − 3²?','[{"key": "A", "text": "1"}, {"key": "B", "text": "5"}, {"key": "C", "text": "7"}, {"key": "D", "text": "13"}]','C','The correct answer is C. 7.','elementary'),
('General Education','Mathematics','medium','Which of the following is an irrational number?','[{"key": "A", "text": "0.5"}, {"key": "B", "text": "1/4"}, {"key": "C", "text": "\u221a3"}, {"key": "D", "text": "2.0"}]','C','The correct answer is C. √3.','elementary'),
('General Education','Mathematics','medium','The sum of interior angles in a triangle equals:','[{"key": "A", "text": "90\u00b0"}, {"key": "B", "text": "180\u00b0"}, {"key": "C", "text": "270\u00b0"}, {"key": "D", "text": "360\u00b0"}]','B','The correct answer is B. 180°.','elementary'),
('General Education','Science','medium','Which blood type is the universal donor?','[{"key": "A", "text": "Type A"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Type B"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Type AB"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Type O"}]','D','The correct answer is D. Type O.','elementary'),
('General Education','Science','medium','Plants release oxygen as a byproduct of:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Respiration"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Transpiration"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Photosynthesis"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Decomposition"}]','C','The correct answer is C. Photosynthesis.','elementary'),
('General Education','Science','medium','What is the chemical formula for water?','[{"key": "A", "text": "H\u2082O\u2082"}, {"key": "B", "text": "HO"}, {"key": "C", "text": "H\u2082O"}, {"key": "D", "text": "OH\u2082"}]','C','The correct answer is C. H₂O.','elementary'),
('General Education','Science','medium','A lunar eclipse occurs when:','[{"key": "A", "text": "The Moon passes between the Earth and the Sun"}, {"key": "B", "text": "The Earth passes between the Sun and the Moon"}, {"key": "C", "text": "The Sun is blocked by clouds"}, {"key": "D", "text": "The Moon is on the far side of the Sun"}]','B','The correct answer is B. The Earth passes between the Sun and the Moon.','elementary'),
('General Education','Science','medium','Which class of lever has the fulcrum in the middle?','[{"key": "A", "text": "First-class lever"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Second-class lever"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Third-class lever"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Fourth-class lever"}]','A','The correct answer is A. First-class lever.','elementary'),
('General Education','Science','medium','Decomposers in an ecosystem are important because they:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Produce food through photosynthesis"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Hunt prey for energy"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Break down dead organisms and return nutrients to the soil"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Purify water"}]','C','The correct answer is C. Break down dead organisms and return nutrients to the soil.','elementary'),
('General Education','Science','medium','The ozone layer protects Earth from:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Infrared radiation"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Ultraviolet (UV) radiation"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Radio waves"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Cosmic rays"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Ultraviolet (UV) radiation.','elementary'),
('General Education','Social Studies','medium','The first Filipino canonized saints are:','[{"key": "A", "text": "San Lorenzo Ruiz only"}, {"key": "B", "text": "San Pedro Calungsod only"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Both San Lorenzo Ruiz and San Pedro Calungsod"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Neither"}]','C','The correct answer is C. Both San Lorenzo Ruiz and San Pedro Calungsod.','elementary'),
('General Education','Social Studies','medium','Apolinario Mabini is known as:','[{"key": "A", "text": "The Great Plebeian"}, {"key": "B", "text": "The Brains of the Revolution"}, {"key": "C", "text": "The Father of the Nation"}, {"key": "D", "text": "The First President"}]','B','The correct answer is B. The Brains of the Revolution.','elementary'),
('General Education','Social Studies','medium','The official capital of the Philippines is:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Cebu City"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Davao City"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Manila"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Quezon City"}]','C','The correct answer is C. Manila.','elementary'),
('General Education','Social Studies','medium','The Filipino practice of ''mano po'' shows:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Greeting strangers"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Respect for elders"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Asking for forgiveness"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Saying goodbye"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Respect for elders.','elementary'),
('General Education','Social Studies','medium','The Industrial Revolution began in:','[{"key": "A", "text": "France"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Germany"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Great Britain"}, {"key": "D", "text": "United States"}]','C','The correct answer is C. Great Britain.','elementary'),
('General Education','Social Studies','medium','The Vice President of the Philippines is elected:','[{"key": "A", "text": "By the President"}, {"key": "B", "text": "By the Congress"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Separately by popular vote"}, {"key": "D", "text": "By the Supreme Court"}]','C','The correct answer is C. Separately by popular vote.','elementary'),
('General Education','Social Studies','medium','Inflation means:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Economic growth"}, {"key": "B", "text": "A general rise in prices over time"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Decrease in wages"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Unemployment"}]','B','The correct answer is B. A general rise in prices over time.','elementary'),
('General Education','Social Studies','medium','Which international organization is responsible for maintaining world peace?','[{"key": "A", "text": "ASEAN only"}, {"key": "B", "text": "United Nations"}, {"key": "C", "text": "World Trade Organization"}, {"key": "D", "text": "International Monetary Fund"}]','B','The correct answer is B. United Nations.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','Child and Adolescent Development','medium','A child in Piaget''s Sensorimotor stage learns primarily through:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Abstract reasoning"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Logical operations"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Senses and physical interactions with the world"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Language and symbols"}]','C','The correct answer is C. Senses and physical interactions with the world.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','Child and Adolescent Development','medium','The key idea in Vygotsky''s theory is that ___ plays a central role in learning:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Heredity"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Social interaction and culture"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Reinforcement"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Individual discovery"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Social interaction and culture.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','Child and Adolescent Development','medium','Which level of Bloom''s Taxonomy is demonstrated when a student compares two historical events?','[{"key": "A", "text": "Remember"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Understand"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Apply"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Analyze"}]','D','The correct answer is D. Analyze.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','Child and Adolescent Development','medium','According to Maslow, self-actualization means:','[{"key": "A", "text": "The most basic need"}, {"key": "B", "text": "The need for friendship"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Reaching one''s full potential"}, {"key": "D", "text": "The need for safety"}]','C','The correct answer is C. Reaching one''s full potential.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','Child and Adolescent Development','medium','Punishment in behaviorism is used to:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Strengthen a behavior"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Weaken or eliminate a behavior"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Teach new behaviors"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Reward achievement"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Weaken or eliminate a behavior.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','Child and Adolescent Development','medium','Ausubel''s theory of meaningful learning emphasizes:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Rote memorization"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Connecting new knowledge to existing (prior) knowledge"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Social interaction"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Physical activity"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Connecting new knowledge to existing (prior) knowledge.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','Child and Adolescent Development','medium','Thorndike''s ''Law of Exercise'' states that:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Physical exercise is required for learning"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Repeated practice strengthens learning"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Students need PE to study well"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Rewards must be given during exercises"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Repeated practice strengthens learning.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','Principles of Teaching','medium','A teacher writing objectives starting with ''The student will appreciate...'' is targeting the ___ domain:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Cognitive"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Psychomotor"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Affective"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Social"}]','C','The correct answer is C. Affective.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','Principles of Teaching','medium','Which of the following is a student-centered instructional strategy?','[{"key": "A", "text": "Lecture"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Project-based learning"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Recitation drill"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Teacher demonstration only"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Project-based learning.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','Principles of Teaching','medium','Criterion-referenced assessment compares student performance to:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Other students'' performance"}, {"key": "B", "text": "National averages"}, {"key": "C", "text": "A fixed set of criteria or standards"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Teacher expectations"}]','C','The correct answer is C. A fixed set of criteria or standards.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','Principles of Teaching','hard','The Tyler Rationale in curriculum development begins with:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Evaluation"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Learning experiences"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Educational purposes / objectives"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Organization of content"}]','C','The correct answer is C. Educational purposes / objectives.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','Principles of Teaching','hard','''Proximity control'' in classroom management means:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Controlling students by proximity to screens"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Moving near a misbehaving student to signal awareness"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Keeping students at arm''s length"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Assigning seats far from troublemakers"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Moving near a misbehaving student to signal awareness.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','Principles of Teaching','hard','An example of a visual instructional material is:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Audio recording"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Podcast"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Concept map"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Role play"}]','C','The correct answer is C. Concept map.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','Principles of Teaching','hard','In the ASSURE model, ''R'' stands for:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Review"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Require learner participation"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Record outcomes"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Reflect on learning"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Require learner participation.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','The Teaching Profession','hard','Using personal social media to mock a student is:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Acceptable if the student is unnamed"}, {"key": "B", "text": "A violation of professional ethics and student rights"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Allowed as freedom of expression"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Only an issue if the school finds out"}]','B','The correct answer is B. A violation of professional ethics and student rights.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','The Teaching Profession','hard','The LET examination for teachers is administered by:','[{"key": "A", "text": "DepEd"}, {"key": "B", "text": "CHED"}, {"key": "C", "text": "PRC"}, {"key": "D", "text": "CSC"}]','C','The correct answer is C. PRC.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','The Teaching Profession','hard','The Philippine Professional Standards for Teachers (PPST) identifies ___ career stages:','[{"key": "A", "text": "2"}, {"key": "B", "text": "3"}, {"key": "C", "text": "4"}, {"key": "D", "text": "5"}]','C','The correct answer is C. 4.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','The Teaching Profession','hard','A teacher who uses corporal punishment violates:','[{"key": "A", "text": "School rules only"}, {"key": "B", "text": "RA 7610 \u2014 Special Protection of Children Against Abuse Act"}, {"key": "C", "text": "RA 7836"}, {"key": "D", "text": "RA 4670"}]','B','The correct answer is B. RA 7610 — Special Protection of Children Against Abuse Act.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','The Teaching Profession','hard','''Sustainable development'' in education means:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Teaching students about money"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Educating for environmental and social responsibility for future generations"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Building more schools"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Increasing school budgets"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Educating for environmental and social responsibility for future generations.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','The Teaching Profession','hard','The school''s role in the community is BEST described as:','[{"key": "A", "text": "A place only for academic learning"}, {"key": "B", "text": "A center for community development and civic engagement"}, {"key": "C", "text": "A government office"}, {"key": "D", "text": "A business organization"}]','B','The correct answer is B. A center for community development and civic engagement.','elementary'),
('General Education','English','easy','''Although it was raining, she went to school'' is a:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Simple sentence"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Compound sentence"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Complex sentence"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Compound-complex sentence"}]','C','The correct answer is C. Complex sentence.','elementary'),
('General Education','English','easy','The word ''philanthropy'' means:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Love of learning"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Love of nature"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Love of humanity / charitable giving"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Love of art"}]','C','The correct answer is C. Love of humanity / charitable giving.','elementary'),
('General Education','English','easy','Which figure of speech uses exaggeration for emphasis?','[{"key": "A", "text": "Simile"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Metaphor"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Hyperbole"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Irony"}]','C','The correct answer is C. Hyperbole.','elementary'),
('General Education','English','easy','A word that joins clauses or sentences is a:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Pronoun"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Preposition"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Conjunction"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Interjection"}]','C','The correct answer is C. Conjunction.','elementary'),
('General Education','English','easy','In ''The boy who studied hard passed the test,'' ''who studied hard'' is a:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Noun phrase"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Adjective clause"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Adverb clause"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Prepositional phrase"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Adjective clause.','elementary'),
('General Education','English','easy','Which word is the adverb in: ''She speaks softly''?','[{"key": "A", "text": "She"}, {"key": "B", "text": "speaks"}, {"key": "C", "text": "softly"}, {"key": "D", "text": "None of the above"}]','C','The correct answer is C. softly.','elementary'),
('General Education','English','easy','Which of the following is a concrete noun?','[{"key": "A", "text": "Love"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Freedom"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Table"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Justice"}]','C','The correct answer is C. Table.','elementary'),
('General Education','English','easy','The purpose of expository writing is to:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Tell a story"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Describe a person"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Explain or inform"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Persuade the reader"}]','C','The correct answer is C. Explain or inform.','elementary'),
('General Education','Mathematics','medium','A number is divisible by 9 if:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Its last digit is 9"}, {"key": "B", "text": "The sum of its digits is divisible by 9"}, {"key": "C", "text": "It ends in 0 or 9"}, {"key": "D", "text": "It is an odd number"}]','B','The correct answer is B. The sum of its digits is divisible by 9.','elementary'),
('General Education','Mathematics','medium','Simple interest on ₱5,000 at 6% per year for 2 years:','[{"key": "A", "text": "\u20b1300"}, {"key": "B", "text": "\u20b1500"}, {"key": "C", "text": "\u20b1600"}, {"key": "D", "text": "\u20b11,200"}]','C','The correct answer is C. ₱600.','elementary'),
('General Education','Mathematics','medium','What is the square root of 144?','[{"key": "A", "text": "11"}, {"key": "B", "text": "12"}, {"key": "C", "text": "13"}, {"key": "D", "text": "14"}]','B','The correct answer is B. 12.','elementary'),
('General Education','Mathematics','medium','Maria has 3× as many books as Ana. Together they have 48. How many does Ana have?','[{"key": "A", "text": "12"}, {"key": "B", "text": "16"}, {"key": "C", "text": "36"}, {"key": "D", "text": "24"}]','A','The correct answer is A. 12.','elementary'),
('General Education','Mathematics','medium','What is the value of (−3)²?','[{"key": "A", "text": "-9"}, {"key": "B", "text": "-6"}, {"key": "C", "text": "6"}, {"key": "D", "text": "9"}]','D','The correct answer is D. 9.','elementary'),
('General Education','Mathematics','medium','The ratio of boys to girls is 3:2. If there are 30 students, how many are boys?','[{"key": "A", "text": "12"}, {"key": "B", "text": "15"}, {"key": "C", "text": "18"}, {"key": "D", "text": "20"}]','C','The correct answer is C. 18.','elementary'),
('General Education','Mathematics','medium','Express 45% as a fraction in lowest terms:','[{"key": "A", "text": "45/100"}, {"key": "B", "text": "9/20"}, {"key": "C", "text": "4/5"}, {"key": "D", "text": "5/9"}]','B','The correct answer is B. 9/20.','elementary'),
('General Education','Science','medium','The human skeleton has approximately ___ bones:','[{"key": "A", "text": "106"}, {"key": "B", "text": "206"}, {"key": "C", "text": "306"}, {"key": "D", "text": "406"}]','B','The correct answer is B. 206.','elementary'),
('General Education','Science','medium','Mitosis results in:','[{"key": "A", "text": "2 cells with half the chromosomes"}, {"key": "B", "text": "4 cells with half the chromosomes"}, {"key": "C", "text": "2 identical cells with the same number of chromosomes"}, {"key": "D", "text": "1 cell with double chromosomes"}]','C','The correct answer is C. 2 identical cells with the same number of chromosomes.','elementary'),
('General Education','Science','medium','Elements are arranged in the Periodic Table according to:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Alphabetical order"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Atomic mass"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Atomic number"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Date of discovery"}]','C','The correct answer is C. Atomic number.','elementary'),
('General Education','Science','medium','A solar eclipse occurs when:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Earth is between the Sun and Moon"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Moon is between the Earth and Sun"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Sun is between Earth and Moon"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Moon is on the opposite side of Earth from the Sun"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Moon is between the Earth and Sun.','elementary'),
('General Education','Science','medium','The unit of electrical current is:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Volt"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Watt"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Ampere"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Ohm"}]','C','The correct answer is C. Ampere.','elementary'),
('General Education','Science','medium','Which gas makes up the largest portion of Earth''s atmosphere?','[{"key": "A", "text": "Oxygen"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Carbon dioxide"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Hydrogen"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Nitrogen"}]','D','The correct answer is D. Nitrogen.','elementary'),
('General Education','Science','medium','Volcanoes are formed at:','[{"key": "A", "text": "The center of tectonic plates"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Tectonic plate boundaries"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Ocean trenches only"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Near the equator only"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Tectonic plate boundaries.','elementary'),
('General Education','Social Studies','medium','The Treaty of Paris (1898) transferred the Philippines from Spain to:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Great Britain"}, {"key": "B", "text": "France"}, {"key": "C", "text": "United States"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Japan"}]','C','The correct answer is C. United States.','elementary'),
('General Education','Social Studies','medium','Who is the national hero of the Philippines?','[{"key": "A", "text": "Andres Bonifacio"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Emilio Aguinaldo"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Jose Rizal"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Apolinario Mabini"}]','C','The correct answer is C. Jose Rizal.','elementary'),
('General Education','Social Studies','medium','The Philippine Sea is located to the ___ of the Philippines:','[{"key": "A", "text": "West"}, {"key": "B", "text": "East"}, {"key": "C", "text": "North"}, {"key": "D", "text": "South"}]','B','The correct answer is B. East.','elementary'),
('General Education','Social Studies','medium','''Amor propio'' in Filipino culture refers to:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Love of country"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Self-esteem and personal dignity"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Love for family"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Pride in community"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Self-esteem and personal dignity.','elementary'),
('General Education','Social Studies','medium','The Magna Carta (1215) limited the powers of the:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Pope"}, {"key": "B", "text": "English king"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Parliament"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Military"}]','B','The correct answer is B. English king.','elementary'),
('General Education','Social Studies','medium','The power of the courts to interpret laws is called:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Executive power"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Legislative power"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Judicial power"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Constitutional power"}]','C','The correct answer is C. Judicial power.','elementary'),
('General Education','Social Studies','medium','''Scarcity'' in economics means:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Too much of a resource"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Unlimited resources"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Limited resources relative to unlimited wants"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Economic depression"}]','C','The correct answer is C. Limited resources relative to unlimited wants.','elementary'),
('General Education','Social Studies','medium','The Sustainable Development Goals (SDGs) were set by the:','[{"key": "A", "text": "World Bank"}, {"key": "B", "text": "United Nations"}, {"key": "C", "text": "ASEAN"}, {"key": "D", "text": "UNESCO"}]','B','The correct answer is B. United Nations.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','Child and Adolescent Development','medium','A 10-year-old who understands conservation of volume is in Piaget''s ___ stage:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Preoperational"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Concrete Operational"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Formal Operational"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Sensorimotor"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Concrete Operational.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','Child and Adolescent Development','medium','According to Vygotsky, the most important tools for cognitive development are:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Physical tools"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Language and cultural symbols"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Toys and games"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Visual aids"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Language and cultural symbols.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','Child and Adolescent Development','medium','A teacher asking students to ''design a solution to reduce plastic waste'' targets which Bloom''s level?','[{"key": "A", "text": "Applying"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Analyzing"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Evaluating"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Creating"}]','D','The correct answer is D. Creating.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','Child and Adolescent Development','medium','Which of Maslow''s needs is MOST related to classroom safety rules?','[{"key": "A", "text": "Physiological"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Safety needs"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Love and belonging"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Esteem"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Safety needs.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','Child and Adolescent Development','medium','In classical conditioning (Pavlov), the conditioned response is:','[{"key": "A", "text": "A natural, unlearned reaction"}, {"key": "B", "text": "A learned reaction to a previously neutral stimulus"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Punishment for bad behavior"}, {"key": "D", "text": "A reward for good behavior"}]','B','The correct answer is B. A learned reaction to a previously neutral stimulus.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','Child and Adolescent Development','medium','Which learning theory emphasizes ''learning by doing''?','[{"key": "A", "text": "Cognitivism"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Experiential learning (Kolb/Dewey)"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Behaviorism"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Nativism"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Experiential learning (Kolb/Dewey).','elementary'),
('Professional Education','Child and Adolescent Development','medium','''Growth mindset'' — the belief that intelligence can be developed — is associated with:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Howard Gardner"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Carol Dweck"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Vygotsky"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Piaget"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Carol Dweck.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','Principles of Teaching','medium','A well-written learning objective should be:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Vague and open-ended"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Specific, measurable, and observable"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Focused on teacher behavior"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Based on teacher preference"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Specific, measurable, and observable.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','Principles of Teaching','medium','The Socratic method involves:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Lecturing to students"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Asking probing questions to stimulate critical thinking"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Showing demonstrations"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Group activities only"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Asking probing questions to stimulate critical thinking.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','Principles of Teaching','medium','Rubrics are MOST useful for assessing:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Multiple choice tests"}, {"key": "B", "text": "True-or-false tests"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Performance tasks and open-ended responses"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Spelling tests"}]','C','The correct answer is C. Performance tasks and open-ended responses.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','Principles of Teaching','hard','The ''hidden curriculum'' refers to:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Secret lessons not approved by DepEd"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Unwritten, implicit values and norms learned in school"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Subjects not in the official curriculum"}, {"key": "D", "text": "After-school activities"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Unwritten, implicit values and norms learned in school.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','Principles of Teaching','hard','A seating arrangement that BEST promotes discussion is:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Rows facing the board"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Horseshoe / U-shape arrangement"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Students facing walls"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Teacher''s desk at center"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Horseshoe / U-shape arrangement.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','Principles of Teaching','hard','Which of the following is a HIGHER-ORDER thinking skill?','[{"key": "A", "text": "Listing facts"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Recalling definitions"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Evaluating arguments"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Identifying names"}]','C','The correct answer is C. Evaluating arguments.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','Principles of Teaching','hard','The term ''andragogy'' refers to the art and science of:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Teaching young children"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Teaching adults"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Teaching special needs students"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Teaching gifted students"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Teaching adults.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','The Teaching Profession','hard','A teacher who arrives late regularly and unprepared is violating:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Academic freedom"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Professional responsibility and commitment"}, {"key": "C", "text": "School policy only"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Personal preference"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Professional responsibility and commitment.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','The Teaching Profession','hard','Continuing Professional Development (CPD) for teachers is required under:','[{"key": "A", "text": "RA 7836 and PRC regulations"}, {"key": "B", "text": "RA 4670"}, {"key": "C", "text": "RA 9155"}, {"key": "D", "text": "DepEd Order only"}]','A','The correct answer is A. RA 7836 and PRC regulations.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','The Teaching Profession','hard','The principle of subsidiarity in education means:','[{"key": "A", "text": "The national government controls all school decisions"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Decisions should be made at the most local level possible"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Private schools control public education"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Teachers make all curriculum decisions"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Decisions should be made at the most local level possible.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','The Teaching Profession','hard','The Governance of Basic Education Act is:','[{"key": "A", "text": "RA 7836"}, {"key": "B", "text": "RA 4670"}, {"key": "C", "text": "RA 9155"}, {"key": "D", "text": "RA 6713"}]','C','The correct answer is C. RA 9155.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','The Teaching Profession','hard','The Philippine Qualifications Framework (PQF) is designed to:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Rank universities"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Standardize levels and outcomes of education and training"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Control teacher salaries"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Regulate private schools"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Standardize levels and outcomes of education and training.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','The Teaching Profession','hard','A teacher who participates in faculty meetings and school activities demonstrates:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Mandatory compliance only"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Active engagement in professional community and school culture"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Obedience to authority"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Fear of disciplinary action"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Active engagement in professional community and school culture.','elementary'),
('General Education','English','easy','Choose the sentence with correct pronoun usage:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Between you and I, this is wrong."}, {"key": "B", "text": "Between you and me, this is wrong."}, {"key": "C", "text": "Between you and myself, this is wrong."}, {"key": "D", "text": "Between I and you, this is wrong."}]','B','The correct answer is B. Between you and me, this is wrong..','elementary'),
('General Education','English','easy','The word ''ambiguous'' means:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Clear and definite"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Open to multiple interpretations"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Extremely important"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Sadly disappointing"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Open to multiple interpretations.','elementary'),
('General Education','English','easy','Which is an example of dramatic irony?','[{"key": "A", "text": "The audience knows something the character does not"}, {"key": "B", "text": "The character uses too many words"}, {"key": "C", "text": "The character uses very few words"}, {"key": "D", "text": "The story ends unexpectedly"}]','A','The correct answer is A. The audience knows something the character does not.','elementary'),
('General Education','English','easy','A word that shows action or state of being is a:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Noun"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Adjective"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Verb"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Adverb"}]','C','The correct answer is C. Verb.','elementary'),
('General Education','English','easy','Which of the following is a complete sentence?','[{"key": "A", "text": "Running through the hallway."}, {"key": "B", "text": "The excited students."}, {"key": "C", "text": "Although she was tired."}, {"key": "D", "text": "The teacher announced the results."}]','D','The correct answer is D. The teacher announced the results..','elementary'),
('General Education','English','easy','Which punctuation mark is used to show possession?','[{"key": "A", "text": "Comma"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Semicolon"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Apostrophe"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Colon"}]','C','The correct answer is C. Apostrophe.','elementary'),
('General Education','English','easy','An essay that uses personal experience to illustrate a larger point is called:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Expository"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Analytical"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Personal / Reflective essay"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Research essay"}]','C','The correct answer is C. Personal / Reflective essay.','elementary'),
('General Education','English','easy','The word ''pedagogy'' refers to:','[{"key": "A", "text": "The study of languages"}, {"key": "B", "text": "The art and science of teaching"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Child development only"}, {"key": "D", "text": "School administration"}]','B','The correct answer is B. The art and science of teaching.','elementary'),
('General Education','Mathematics','medium','The probability of getting HEADS when tossing a fair coin is:','[{"key": "A", "text": "1/4"}, {"key": "B", "text": "1/3"}, {"key": "C", "text": "1/2"}, {"key": "D", "text": "1"}]','C','The correct answer is C. 1/2.','elementary'),
('General Education','Mathematics','medium','Simplify: 18/24','[{"key": "A", "text": "2/3"}, {"key": "B", "text": "3/4"}, {"key": "C", "text": "9/12"}, {"key": "D", "text": "6/8"}]','B','The correct answer is B. 3/4.','elementary'),
('General Education','Mathematics','medium','A rectangle has an area of 48 cm² and a width of 6 cm. What is its length?','[{"key": "A", "text": "6 cm"}, {"key": "B", "text": "7 cm"}, {"key": "C", "text": "8 cm"}, {"key": "D", "text": "9 cm"}]','C','The correct answer is C. 8 cm.','elementary'),
('General Education','Mathematics','medium','Three friends share ₱750 equally. How much does each receive?','[{"key": "A", "text": "\u20b1200"}, {"key": "B", "text": "\u20b1225"}, {"key": "C", "text": "\u20b1250"}, {"key": "D", "text": "\u20b1300"}]','C','The correct answer is C. ₱250.','elementary'),
('General Education','Mathematics','medium','What is 10³?','[{"key": "A", "text": "30"}, {"key": "B", "text": "100"}, {"key": "C", "text": "300"}, {"key": "D", "text": "1,000"}]','D','The correct answer is D. 1,000.','elementary'),
('General Education','Mathematics','medium','Which is the smallest: 1/2, 2/5, 3/8?','[{"key": "A", "text": "1/2"}, {"key": "B", "text": "2/5"}, {"key": "C", "text": "3/8"}, {"key": "D", "text": "They are equal"}]','C','The correct answer is C. 3/8.','elementary'),
('General Education','Mathematics','medium','2 shirts (₱360 each) + 1 pair of pants (₱580). What is the total?','[{"key": "A", "text": "\u20b11,200"}, {"key": "B", "text": "\u20b11,300"}, {"key": "C", "text": "\u20b11,360"}, {"key": "D", "text": "\u20b11,280"}]','B','The correct answer is B. ₱1,300.','elementary'),
('General Education','Science','medium','The brain is part of which organ system?','[{"key": "A", "text": "Circulatory system"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Nervous system"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Endocrine system"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Respiratory system"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Nervous system.','elementary'),
('General Education','Science','medium','Which plant process releases water vapor through the leaves?','[{"key": "A", "text": "Photosynthesis"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Respiration"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Transpiration"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Germination"}]','C','The correct answer is C. Transpiration.','elementary'),
('General Education','Science','medium','Atoms of the same element with different numbers of neutrons are called:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Ions"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Isotopes"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Molecules"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Compounds"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Isotopes.','elementary'),
('General Education','Science','medium','Which of the following is NOT a planet in our solar system?','[{"key": "A", "text": "Mars"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Saturn"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Pluto"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Uranus"}]','C','The correct answer is C. Pluto.','elementary'),
('General Education','Science','medium','Which type of energy is stored in a stretched rubber band?','[{"key": "A", "text": "Kinetic energy"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Chemical energy"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Thermal energy"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Potential energy"}]','D','The correct answer is D. Potential energy.','elementary'),
('General Education','Science','medium','A food chain always begins with:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Carnivores"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Decomposers"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Producers (plants)"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Herbivores"}]','C','The correct answer is C. Producers (plants).','elementary'),
('General Education','Science','medium','Magma that reaches the Earth''s surface is called:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Lava"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Igneous rock"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Sediment"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Mineral"}]','A','The correct answer is A. Lava.','elementary'),
('General Education','Social Studies','medium','The Japanese occupation of the Philippines was during:','[{"key": "A", "text": "1898\u20131901"}, {"key": "B", "text": "1935\u20131941"}, {"key": "C", "text": "1942\u20131945"}, {"key": "D", "text": "1946\u20131950"}]','C','The correct answer is C. 1942–1945.','elementary'),
('General Education','Social Studies','medium','After the Tejeros Convention, the Revolutionary Government was led by:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Andres Bonifacio"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Emilio Aguinaldo"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Apolinario Mabini"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Antonio Luna"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Emilio Aguinaldo.','elementary'),
('General Education','Social Studies','medium','Lake Lanao, one of the largest lakes in the Philippines, is located in:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Luzon"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Visayas"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Mindanao"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Palawan"}]','C','The correct answer is C. Mindanao.','elementary'),
('General Education','Social Studies','medium','''Ningas-cogon'' is a Filipino trait that refers to:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Strong perseverance"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Initial enthusiasm that quickly fades"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Community cooperation"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Respect for authority"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Initial enthusiasm that quickly fades.','elementary'),
('General Education','Social Studies','medium','The Cold War was a conflict between:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Germany and France"}, {"key": "B", "text": "United States and Soviet Union"}, {"key": "C", "text": "United States and China"}, {"key": "D", "text": "United Kingdom and Germany"}]','B','The correct answer is B. United States and Soviet Union.','elementary'),
('General Education','Social Studies','medium','The legislative body of the Philippines is the:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Supreme Court"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Cabinet"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Congress (Senate and House of Representatives)"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Executive Department"}]','C','The correct answer is C. Congress (Senate and House of Representatives).','elementary'),
('General Education','Social Studies','medium','The law of supply states that when price rises:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Supply decreases"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Supply increases"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Supply stays the same"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Demand increases"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Supply increases.','elementary'),
('General Education','Social Studies','medium','UNESCO stands for:','[{"key": "A", "text": "United Nations Education, Science and Culture Organization"}, {"key": "B", "text": "United Nations Economic, Social and Cultural Organization"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Universal Nations Educational, Scientific and Cultural Organization"}, {"key": "D", "text": "United Nations Educational, Scientific and Cultural Organization"}]','D','The correct answer is D. United Nations Educational, Scientific and Cultural Organization.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','Child and Adolescent Development','medium','Egocentrism in Piaget''s theory is characteristic of the ___ stage:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Sensorimotor"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Preoperational"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Concrete Operational"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Formal Operational"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Preoperational.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','Child and Adolescent Development','medium','According to Vygotsky, good instruction can pull development forward. This means:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Children must be developmentally ready before learning"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Learning leads development"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Development naturally leads to learning"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Learning and development are unrelated"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Learning leads development.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','Child and Adolescent Development','medium','Which of the following is NOT in Bloom''s cognitive domain?','[{"key": "A", "text": "Creating"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Evaluating"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Receiving"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Analyzing"}]','C','The correct answer is C. Receiving.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','Child and Adolescent Development','medium','Which Maslow need involves feeling respected and valued by others?','[{"key": "A", "text": "Safety"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Love and belonging"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Esteem"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Self-actualization"}]','C','The correct answer is C. Esteem.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','Child and Adolescent Development','medium','Operant conditioning is associated with:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Ivan Pavlov"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Albert Bandura"}, {"key": "C", "text": "B.F. Skinner"}, {"key": "D", "text": "John Dewey"}]','C','The correct answer is C. B.F. Skinner.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','Child and Adolescent Development','medium','The term ''metacognition'' refers to:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Learning through observation"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Thinking about one''s own thinking and learning processes"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Teaching strategies"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Multiple intelligences"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Thinking about one''s own thinking and learning processes.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','Child and Adolescent Development','medium','Which intelligence in Gardner''s theory involves sensitivity to nature and living things?','[{"key": "A", "text": "Spatial"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Bodily-Kinesthetic"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Naturalist"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Musical"}]','C','The correct answer is C. Naturalist.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','Principles of Teaching','medium','A teacher begins class with an activity to activate prior knowledge. This is called a:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Summary"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Motivation / Hook activity"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Formative assessment"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Closure"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Motivation / Hook activity.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','Principles of Teaching','medium','Role-playing as a teaching strategy BEST develops:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Cognitive memorization only"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Affective and social skills"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Reading skills only"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Mathematical skills"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Affective and social skills.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','Principles of Teaching','medium','A test that measures what it is supposed to measure is said to have:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Reliability"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Objectivity"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Validity"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Practicality"}]','C','The correct answer is C. Validity.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','Principles of Teaching','hard','The process of deciding what to teach, how to teach, and how to assess is called:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Curriculum development"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Instructional design"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Lesson planning"}, {"key": "D", "text": "All of the above"}]','D','The correct answer is D. All of the above.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','Principles of Teaching','hard','A teacher uses eye contact and gestures to manage behavior. This is called:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Physical punishment"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Non-verbal communication cues"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Passive management"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Verbal reprimand"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Non-verbal communication cues.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','Principles of Teaching','hard','Action research in education is conducted to:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Satisfy DepEd requirements"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Improve classroom practice through systematic inquiry"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Publish research papers"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Test students'' abilities"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Improve classroom practice through systematic inquiry.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','Principles of Teaching','hard','Which principle states that learning materials should match the developmental level of learners?','[{"key": "A", "text": "Principle of selectivity"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Principle of readiness"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Principle of evaluation"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Principle of integration"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Principle of readiness.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','The Teaching Profession','hard','The duty to make ''reasonable adjustments'' for students with disabilities reflects:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Extra burden for teachers"}, {"key": "B", "text": "The principle of inclusive education"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Special education philosophy only"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Optional school policy"}]','B','The correct answer is B. The principle of inclusive education.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','The Teaching Profession','hard','Which agency oversees basic education in the Philippines?','[{"key": "A", "text": "CHED"}, {"key": "B", "text": "TESDA"}, {"key": "C", "text": "DepEd"}, {"key": "D", "text": "PRC"}]','C','The correct answer is C. DepEd.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','The Teaching Profession','hard','The ''No Child Left Behind'' principle reflects:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Strict academic standards"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Universal access to quality education for all learners"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Grade retention policies"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Private school preference"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Universal access to quality education for all learners.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','The Teaching Profession','hard','A teacher who earns continuing education units is fulfilling:','[{"key": "A", "text": "A personal hobby"}, {"key": "B", "text": "CPD (Continuing Professional Development) requirements"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Personal ambition"}, {"key": "D", "text": "School policy only"}]','B','The correct answer is B. CPD (Continuing Professional Development) requirements.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','The Teaching Profession','hard','''Whole child development'' includes:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Academic achievement only"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Physical, cognitive, social, emotional, and spiritual development"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Physical development only"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Cognitive development only"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Physical, cognitive, social, emotional, and spiritual development.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','The Teaching Profession','hard','An effective teacher-community relationship is built on:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Fear and authority"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Mutual respect, communication, and shared goals"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Teacher superiority"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Financial incentives"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Mutual respect, communication, and shared goals.','elementary'),
('General Education','English','easy','Which sentence contains a dangling modifier?','[{"key": "A", "text": "While walking to school, Maria got caught in the rain."}, {"key": "B", "text": "Walking to school, the rain started to fall."}, {"key": "C", "text": "Maria got wet walking home."}, {"key": "D", "text": "The rain fell while Maria walked to school."}]','B','The correct answer is B. Walking to school, the rain started to fall..','elementary'),
('General Education','English','easy','The word ''ephemeral'' means:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Eternal"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Short-lived; lasting a very short time"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Extremely large"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Deeply emotional"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Short-lived; lasting a very short time.','elementary'),
('General Education','English','easy','Which sentence correctly uses a colon?','[{"key": "A", "text": "She bought: apples, mangoes, and grapes."}, {"key": "B", "text": "She is: a teacher."}, {"key": "C", "text": "She needs three things: patience, practice, and perseverance."}, {"key": "D", "text": "She: studied hard."}]','C','The correct answer is C. She needs three things: patience, practice, and perseverance..','elementary'),
('General Education','English','easy','''The pen is mightier than the sword'' is an example of:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Alliteration"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Onomatopoeia"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Metaphor"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Personification"}]','C','The correct answer is C. Metaphor.','elementary'),
('General Education','English','easy','Which of the following is an abstract noun?','[{"key": "A", "text": "Chair"}, {"key": "B", "text": "River"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Freedom"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Tree"}]','C','The correct answer is C. Freedom.','elementary'),
('General Education','English','easy','The prefix ''pre-'' in ''prehistoric'' means:','[{"key": "A", "text": "After"}, {"key": "B", "text": "During"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Before"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Without"}]','C','The correct answer is C. Before.','elementary'),
('General Education','English','easy','Which type of context clue defines the word within the same sentence?','[{"key": "A", "text": "Synonym clue"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Definition/Appositive clue"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Antonym clue"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Example clue"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Definition/Appositive clue.','elementary'),
('General Education','English','easy','''She read the book quickly, carefully, and thoroughly.'' The underlined words are:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Adjectives"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Adverbs"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Conjunctions"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Prepositions"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Adverbs.','elementary'),
('General Education','Mathematics','medium','What is the LCM of 8 and 12?','[{"key": "A", "text": "4"}, {"key": "B", "text": "16"}, {"key": "C", "text": "24"}, {"key": "D", "text": "48"}]','C','The correct answer is C. 24.','elementary'),
('General Education','Mathematics','medium','A car uses 8 liters of gasoline per 100 km. How many liters are needed for 250 km?','[{"key": "A", "text": "16"}, {"key": "B", "text": "18"}, {"key": "C", "text": "20"}, {"key": "D", "text": "24"}]','C','The correct answer is C. 20.','elementary'),
('General Education','Mathematics','medium','Which of the following is NOT a prime number?','[{"key": "A", "text": "2"}, {"key": "B", "text": "11"}, {"key": "C", "text": "23"}, {"key": "D", "text": "27"}]','D','The correct answer is D. 27.','elementary'),
('General Education','Mathematics','medium','A class has 35 students; 60% are girls. How many boys are there?','[{"key": "A", "text": "14"}, {"key": "B", "text": "21"}, {"key": "C", "text": "24"}, {"key": "D", "text": "10"}]','A','The correct answer is A. 14.','elementary'),
('General Education','Mathematics','medium','The surface area of a cube with side 3 cm is:','[{"key": "A", "text": "9 cm\u00b2"}, {"key": "B", "text": "27 cm\u00b2"}, {"key": "C", "text": "54 cm\u00b2"}, {"key": "D", "text": "18 cm\u00b2"}]','C','The correct answer is C. 54 cm².','elementary'),
('General Education','Mathematics','medium','A train departed at 8:00 AM and arrived at 11:30 AM, traveling 210 km. What is its average speed?','[{"key": "A", "text": "50 km/h"}, {"key": "B", "text": "60 km/h"}, {"key": "C", "text": "70 km/h"}, {"key": "D", "text": "80 km/h"}]','B','The correct answer is B. 60 km/h.','elementary'),
('General Education','Mathematics','medium','What is 40% of 250?','[{"key": "A", "text": "80"}, {"key": "B", "text": "90"}, {"key": "C", "text": "100"}, {"key": "D", "text": "110"}]','C','The correct answer is C. 100.','elementary'),
('General Education','Science','medium','Which of the following is NOT an example of a chemical change?','[{"key": "A", "text": "Burning wood"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Rusting iron"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Cutting paper"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Souring milk"}]','C','The correct answer is C. Cutting paper.','elementary'),
('General Education','Science','medium','The smallest unit of an element that retains its chemical properties is the:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Molecule"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Compound"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Atom"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Electron"}]','C','The correct answer is C. Atom.','elementary'),
('General Education','Science','medium','Which type of rock is formed from cooled magma or lava?','[{"key": "A", "text": "Sedimentary"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Metamorphic"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Igneous"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Limestone"}]','C','The correct answer is C. Igneous.','elementary'),
('General Education','Science','medium','Force per unit area is called:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Density"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Pressure"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Velocity"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Momentum"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Pressure.','elementary'),
('General Education','Science','medium','Which organ filters waste from blood to produce urine?','[{"key": "A", "text": "Liver"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Lungs"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Kidneys"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Pancreas"}]','C','The correct answer is C. Kidneys.','elementary'),
('General Education','Science','medium','What is the correct order of the water cycle?','[{"key": "A", "text": "Precipitation \u2192 Evaporation \u2192 Condensation"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Evaporation \u2192 Condensation \u2192 Precipitation"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Condensation \u2192 Precipitation \u2192 Evaporation"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Precipitation \u2192 Condensation \u2192 Evaporation"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Evaporation → Condensation → Precipitation.','elementary'),
('General Education','Science','medium','The boiling point of water at sea level is:','[{"key": "A", "text": "90\u00b0C"}, {"key": "B", "text": "95\u00b0C"}, {"key": "C", "text": "100\u00b0C"}, {"key": "D", "text": "110\u00b0C"}]','C','The correct answer is C. 100°C.','elementary'),
('General Education','Social Studies','medium','The first Catholic Mass in the Philippines was celebrated in:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Cebu"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Manila"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Limasawa, Leyte"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Mactan, Cebu"}]','C','The correct answer is C. Limasawa, Leyte.','elementary'),
('General Education','Social Studies','medium','The famous painting ''Spoliarium'' was created by:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Botong Francisco"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Juan Luna"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Felix Resurreccion Hidalgo"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Guillermo Tolentino"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Juan Luna.','elementary'),
('General Education','Social Studies','medium','Mindanao is sometimes called the ''Land of Promise'' because of its:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Historical significance"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Fertile agricultural land and rich natural resources"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Famous tourist spots"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Large urban population"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Fertile agricultural land and rich natural resources.','elementary'),
('General Education','Social Studies','medium','''Utang na loob'' (debt of gratitude) means:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Monetary debt"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Moral obligation to repay help or kindness received"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Government debt"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Tax obligation"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Moral obligation to repay help or kindness received.','elementary'),
('General Education','Social Studies','medium','The United Nations was founded in:','[{"key": "A", "text": "1939"}, {"key": "B", "text": "1945"}, {"key": "C", "text": "1950"}, {"key": "D", "text": "1919"}]','B','The correct answer is B. 1945.','elementary'),
('General Education','Social Studies','medium','The Preamble to the Philippine Constitution begins with:','[{"key": "A", "text": "''We, the citizens of the Philippines...''"}, {"key": "B", "text": "''We, the people of the Philippines...''"}, {"key": "C", "text": "''We, the sovereign people of the Philippines...''"}, {"key": "D", "text": "''We, the Filipino people...''"}]','B','The correct answer is B. ''We, the people of the Philippines...''.','elementary'),
('General Education','Social Studies','medium','''Monopoly'' in economics refers to:','[{"key": "A", "text": "A market with many sellers"}, {"key": "B", "text": "A market dominated by one seller with no competition"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Government control of all businesses"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Free market competition"}]','B','The correct answer is B. A market dominated by one seller with no competition.','elementary'),
('General Education','Social Studies','medium','The ''Archipelagic Doctrine'' claims that:','[{"key": "A", "text": "The Philippines is the largest island nation"}, {"key": "B", "text": "All waters between Philippine islands are part of its territory"}, {"key": "C", "text": "The Philippines has exclusive fishing rights beyond 200 miles"}, {"key": "D", "text": "The Philippines controls all nearby international waters"}]','B','The correct answer is B. All waters between Philippine islands are part of its territory.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','Child and Adolescent Development','medium','In Piaget''s theory, ''assimilation'' means:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Changing existing schemas to accommodate new info"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Incorporating new information into existing mental schemas"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Forgetting old information"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Creating entirely new schemas"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Incorporating new information into existing mental schemas.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','Child and Adolescent Development','medium','''Scaffolding'' in Vygotsky''s theory refers to:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Building physical structures in school"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Temporary support given to a learner until they can work independently"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Organizing classroom furniture"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Creating lesson plans"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Temporary support given to a learner until they can work independently.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','Child and Adolescent Development','medium','The affective domain in Bloom''s taxonomy involves:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Physical skills and coordination"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Knowledge and mental skills"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Attitudes, feelings, and values"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Language development"}]','C','The correct answer is C. Attitudes, feelings, and values.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','Child and Adolescent Development','medium','Erik Erikson''s theory of development focuses on:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Cognitive stages"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Psychosocial stages across the lifespan"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Language acquisition"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Moral development"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Psychosocial stages across the lifespan.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','Child and Adolescent Development','medium','Which of the following is an example of intrinsic motivation?','[{"key": "A", "text": "Studying to get a high grade"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Studying because you genuinely enjoy learning"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Studying to please your parents"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Studying to avoid punishment"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Studying because you genuinely enjoy learning.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','Child and Adolescent Development','medium','Lawrence Kohlberg''s theory deals with:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Cognitive development"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Moral development"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Language acquisition"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Social development"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Moral development.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','Child and Adolescent Development','medium','Which of Gardner''s intelligences involves deep understanding of oneself?','[{"key": "A", "text": "Interpersonal"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Intrapersonal"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Linguistic"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Logical-Mathematical"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Intrapersonal.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','Principles of Teaching','medium','A teacher who uses ''exit tickets'' at the end of class is doing:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Summative assessment"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Formative assessment (checking for understanding)"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Portfolio assessment"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Standardized testing"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Formative assessment (checking for understanding).','elementary'),
('Professional Education','Principles of Teaching','medium','Which strategy involves students working together toward a shared learning goal?','[{"key": "A", "text": "Individual recitation"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Cooperative learning"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Direct instruction"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Rote memorization"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Cooperative learning.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','Principles of Teaching','medium','Norm-referenced assessment compares a student''s performance to:','[{"key": "A", "text": "A fixed standard"}, {"key": "B", "text": "The performance of other students in the group"}, {"key": "C", "text": "The teacher''s expectations"}, {"key": "D", "text": "National curriculum goals"}]','B','The correct answer is B. The performance of other students in the group.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','Principles of Teaching','hard','''Begin with the end in mind'' in curriculum design refers to:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Teaching from the last chapter first"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Backward design \u2014 starting with desired outcomes"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Planning final exams first"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Teaching the most important topics last"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Backward design — starting with desired outcomes.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','Principles of Teaching','hard','Which classroom management strategy gives students ownership of behavior?','[{"key": "A", "text": "Teacher dictates all rules"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Involving students in creating classroom rules"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Using strict punishments"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Assigning permanent seats"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Involving students in creating classroom rules.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','Principles of Teaching','hard','Which of the following is an example of technology-integrated instruction?','[{"key": "A", "text": "Reading textbooks only"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Using video presentations and educational apps in lessons"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Giving oral recitations daily"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Having students write in notebooks only"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Using video presentations and educational apps in lessons.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','Principles of Teaching','hard','Peer tutoring is effective primarily because:','[{"key": "A", "text": "It reduces the teacher''s workload"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Students often explain concepts in ways peers can relate to"}, {"key": "C", "text": "It replaces teacher instruction"}, {"key": "D", "text": "It is required by the curriculum"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Students often explain concepts in ways peers can relate to.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','The Teaching Profession','hard','A teacher absent frequently without valid reason is violating:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Academic freedom"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Professional responsibility and commitment to learners"}, {"key": "C", "text": "School rule only"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Personal preference"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Professional responsibility and commitment to learners.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','The Teaching Profession','hard','RA 9293 (amending RA 7836) mainly:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Increased teacher salaries"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Removed the professional education unit requirement for non-education graduates taking the LET"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Created the Code of Ethics"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Established CHED"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Removed the professional education unit requirement for non-education graduates taking the LET.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','The Teaching Profession','hard','The ''Code of Ethics for Professional Teachers'' was issued by:','[{"key": "A", "text": "DepEd"}, {"key": "B", "text": "CHED"}, {"key": "C", "text": "PRC / Board of Professional Teachers"}, {"key": "D", "text": "CSC"}]','C','The correct answer is C. PRC / Board of Professional Teachers.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','The Teaching Profession','hard','A teacher who discriminates against students based on religion is violating:','[{"key": "A", "text": "School policy only"}, {"key": "B", "text": "The Bill of Rights (equal protection) and the Code of Ethics"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Academic freedom"}, {"key": "D", "text": "RA 7836"}]','B','The correct answer is B. The Bill of Rights (equal protection) and the Code of Ethics.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','The Teaching Profession','hard','''Academic freedom'' means:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Students can ignore school rules"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Teachers and institutions have freedom to pursue knowledge without undue external interference"}, {"key": "C", "text": "School is free of charge"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Teachers can teach anything without accountability"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Teachers and institutions have freedom to pursue knowledge without undue external interference.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','The Teaching Profession','hard','Which RA established the Commission on Higher Education (CHED)?','[{"key": "A", "text": "RA 7722"}, {"key": "B", "text": "RA 7836"}, {"key": "C", "text": "RA 9155"}, {"key": "D", "text": "RA 8981"}]','A','The correct answer is A. RA 7722.','elementary'),
('General Education','English','easy','''Neither the students nor the teacher was prepared.'' This sentence is:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Incorrect \u2014 it should be ''were prepared''"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Correct \u2014 ''teacher'' is nearest the verb so singular ''was'' is used"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Incorrect \u2014 it should use ''either...or''"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Correct but only when ''nor'' is used with plural nouns"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Correct — ''teacher'' is nearest the verb so singular ''was'' is used.','elementary'),
('General Education','English','easy','The word ''loquacious'' means:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Very quiet"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Very talkative"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Extremely intelligent"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Easily angered"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Very talkative.','elementary'),
('General Education','English','easy','''Running is good exercise.'' ''Running'' here is a:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Gerund (verb form used as a noun)"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Participle modifying a noun"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Infinitive"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Present continuous verb"}]','A','The correct answer is A. Gerund (verb form used as a noun).','elementary'),
('General Education','English','easy','''Do you want to eat or sleep first?'' is a ___ sentence:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Declarative"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Exclamatory"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Imperative"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Interrogative"}]','D','The correct answer is D. Interrogative.','elementary'),
('General Education','English','easy','The literary term ''flashback'' means:','[{"key": "A", "text": "A fast-paced section of the story"}, {"key": "B", "text": "A scene set in an earlier time that interrupts the current narrative"}, {"key": "C", "text": "A preview of future events"}, {"key": "D", "text": "A comparison between two things"}]','B','The correct answer is B. A scene set in an earlier time that interrupts the current narrative.','elementary'),
('General Education','English','easy','''A blessing in disguise'' is a/an:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Idiom"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Metaphor"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Alliteration"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Hyperbole"}]','A','The correct answer is A. Idiom.','elementary'),
('General Education','English','easy','Which type of essay provides clear, organized information about a topic?','[{"key": "A", "text": "Narrative"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Persuasive"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Expository"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Descriptive"}]','C','The correct answer is C. Expository.','elementary'),
('General Education','English','easy','''Which word means the OPPOSITE of ''diligent''?','[{"key": "A", "text": "Hardworking"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Careful"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Lazy"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Attentive"}]','C','The correct answer is C. Lazy.','elementary'),
('General Education','Mathematics','medium','Evaluate: 3 + 4 × 2 − 1 (using PEMDAS)','[{"key": "A", "text": "13"}, {"key": "B", "text": "10"}, {"key": "C", "text": "14"}, {"key": "D", "text": "12"}]','B','The correct answer is B. 10.','elementary'),
('General Education','Mathematics','medium','A jacket costs ₱1,200. After a 15% discount, how much does it cost?','[{"key": "A", "text": "\u20b11,020"}, {"key": "B", "text": "\u20b11,050"}, {"key": "C", "text": "\u20b11,080"}, {"key": "D", "text": "\u20b11,100"}]','A','The correct answer is A. ₱1,020.','elementary'),
('General Education','Mathematics','medium','The interior angles of a quadrilateral sum to:','[{"key": "A", "text": "180\u00b0"}, {"key": "B", "text": "270\u00b0"}, {"key": "C", "text": "360\u00b0"}, {"key": "D", "text": "540\u00b0"}]','C','The correct answer is C. 360°.','elementary'),
('General Education','Mathematics','medium','5 workers build a wall in 12 days. How many days will 10 workers take?','[{"key": "A", "text": "3"}, {"key": "B", "text": "4"}, {"key": "C", "text": "6"}, {"key": "D", "text": "8"}]','C','The correct answer is C. 6.','elementary'),
('General Education','Mathematics','medium','What is 2⁵?','[{"key": "A", "text": "10"}, {"key": "B", "text": "16"}, {"key": "C", "text": "25"}, {"key": "D", "text": "32"}]','D','The correct answer is D. 32.','elementary'),
('General Education','Mathematics','medium','Write 0.08 as a fraction in lowest terms:','[{"key": "A", "text": "8/10"}, {"key": "B", "text": "4/50"}, {"key": "C", "text": "2/25"}, {"key": "D", "text": "1/12"}]','C','The correct answer is C. 2/25.','elementary'),
('General Education','Mathematics','medium','The range of the data set {4, 7, 2, 9, 5, 1} is:','[{"key": "A", "text": "7"}, {"key": "B", "text": "8"}, {"key": "C", "text": "9"}, {"key": "D", "text": "5"}]','B','The correct answer is B. 8.','elementary'),
('General Education','Science','medium','Which planet is known as the ''Red Planet''?','[{"key": "A", "text": "Jupiter"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Venus"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Mars"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Saturn"}]','C','The correct answer is C. Mars.','elementary'),
('General Education','Science','medium','Which type of bond holds water molecules (H₂O) to each other?','[{"key": "A", "text": "Ionic bond"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Covalent bond"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Hydrogen bond"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Metallic bond"}]','C','The correct answer is C. Hydrogen bond.','elementary'),
('General Education','Science','medium','The principle that matter cannot be created or destroyed is:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Newton''s First Law"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Law of Conservation of Mass"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Law of Conservation of Energy"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Boyle''s Law"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Law of Conservation of Mass.','elementary'),
('General Education','Science','medium','Which organ produces insulin to regulate blood sugar?','[{"key": "A", "text": "Liver"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Stomach"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Pancreas"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Gallbladder"}]','C','The correct answer is C. Pancreas.','elementary'),
('General Education','Science','medium','Convex lenses are used to correct:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Nearsightedness only"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Farsightedness and in magnifying glasses"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Color blindness"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Astigmatism"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Farsightedness and in magnifying glasses.','elementary'),
('General Education','Science','medium','A mixture where components can be easily separated (like sand and water) is:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Solution"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Compound"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Heterogeneous mixture"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Homogeneous mixture"}]','C','The correct answer is C. Heterogeneous mixture.','elementary'),
('General Education','Science','medium','The bending of light when it passes from one medium to another is:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Reflection"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Refraction"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Diffraction"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Absorption"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Refraction.','elementary'),
('General Education','Social Studies','medium','''El Filibusterismo'' (The Reign of Greed) was written by:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Andres Bonifacio"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Marcelo del Pilar"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Jose Rizal"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Claro M. Recto"}]','C','The correct answer is C. Jose Rizal.','elementary'),
('General Education','Social Studies','medium','The Philippine-American War began in:','[{"key": "A", "text": "1896"}, {"key": "B", "text": "1898"}, {"key": "C", "text": "1899"}, {"key": "D", "text": "1901"}]','C','The correct answer is C. 1899.','elementary'),
('General Education','Social Studies','medium','The Visayas region of the Philippines includes:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Luzon, Palawan, and Mindoro"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Cebu, Bohol, Leyte, Samar, Negros, and Panay"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Mindanao, Basilan, and Sulu"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Batanes and Cagayan"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Cebu, Bohol, Leyte, Samar, Negros, and Panay.','elementary'),
('General Education','Social Studies','medium','''Bayanihan'' literally refers to:','[{"key": "A", "text": "A type of Filipino dance"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Neighbors cooperating to help a family move their house"}, {"key": "C", "text": "A Filipino festival"}, {"key": "D", "text": "A type of Filipino food"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Neighbors cooperating to help a family move their house.','elementary'),
('General Education','Social Studies','medium','Who was the FIRST woman President of the Philippines?','[{"key": "A", "text": "Gloria Macapagal-Arroyo"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Corazon Aquino"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Miriam Defensor Santiago"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Leni Robredo"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Corazon Aquino.','elementary'),
('General Education','Social Studies','medium','Federalism is a system of government where:','[{"key": "A", "text": "One person holds all power"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Power is divided between central and regional governments"}, {"key": "C", "text": "The military controls the government"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Only the legislature has power"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Power is divided between central and regional governments.','elementary'),
('General Education','Social Studies','medium','Tariff in economics refers to:','[{"key": "A", "text": "A tax on income"}, {"key": "B", "text": "A tax on imported goods"}, {"key": "C", "text": "A fee for government services"}, {"key": "D", "text": "A fine for violations"}]','B','The correct answer is B. A tax on imported goods.','elementary'),
('General Education','Social Studies','medium','The Geneva Conventions primarily deal with:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Trade agreements"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Treatment of prisoners of war and civilians in conflict"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Environmental protection"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Nuclear weapons"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Treatment of prisoners of war and civilians in conflict.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','Child and Adolescent Development','medium','In Piaget''s theory, ''accommodation'' means:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Incorporating new information into existing schemas"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Modifying existing schemas to fit new information"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Creating entirely new schemas"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Ignoring contradictory information"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Modifying existing schemas to fit new information.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','Child and Adolescent Development','medium','Vygotsky believed that language and thought are:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Completely separate processes"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Deeply interconnected \u2014 language shapes thinking"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Innate and unchangeable"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Developed only through punishment"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Deeply interconnected — language shapes thinking.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','Child and Adolescent Development','medium','The psychomotor domain in Bloom''s taxonomy involves:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Mental processes"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Attitudes and values"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Physical skills and coordination"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Social interaction"}]','C','The correct answer is C. Physical skills and coordination.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','Child and Adolescent Development','medium','In Erikson''s stages, ''Trust vs. Mistrust'' occurs during:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Early childhood (3\u20136 years)"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Infancy (0\u201318 months)"}, {"key": "C", "text": "School age (6\u201312 years)"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Adolescence"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Infancy (0–18 months).','elementary'),
('Professional Education','Child and Adolescent Development','medium','Token economy in behavior management involves:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Using real money to reward students"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Giving symbolic rewards (tokens) that can be exchanged for privileges"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Punishing bad behavior with token removal only"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Making students earn grades through tests only"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Giving symbolic rewards (tokens) that can be exchanged for privileges.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','Child and Adolescent Development','medium','Piaget''s concept of ''equilibration'' refers to:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Equal seating in classrooms"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Balancing assimilation and accommodation to maintain cognitive equilibrium"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Equal treatment of all students"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Balancing study time and rest"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Balancing assimilation and accommodation to maintain cognitive equilibrium.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','Child and Adolescent Development','medium','Gardner''s Bodily-Kinesthetic intelligence is associated with:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Sensitivity to music"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Skill in using one''s body purposefully (athletes, dancers, surgeons)"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Understanding of nature"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Ability to use language effectively"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Skill in using one''s body purposefully (athletes, dancers, surgeons).','elementary'),
('Professional Education','Principles of Teaching','medium','''KWL Chart'' stands for:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Know, Want to know, Learned"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Key Words and Learning"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Knowledge, Work, and Lecture"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Know, Write, and Listen"}]','A','The correct answer is A. Know, Want to know, Learned.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','Principles of Teaching','medium','Which teaching approach is most appropriate for teaching values?','[{"key": "A", "text": "Direct instruction only"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Values clarification and reflective activities"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Rote memorization"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Standardized testing"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Values clarification and reflective activities.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','Principles of Teaching','medium','A test is reliable if it:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Measures what it claims to measure"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Produces consistent results when administered repeatedly"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Is easy to score"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Is short"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Produces consistent results when administered repeatedly.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','Principles of Teaching','hard','Which describes a student-centered classroom?','[{"key": "A", "text": "The teacher talks most of the time"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Students take an active role in their own learning and inquiry"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Textbooks are the main resource"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Grades determine all activity"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Students take an active role in their own learning and inquiry.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','Principles of Teaching','hard','''Wait time'' in teaching means:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Waiting for students to be quiet before teaching"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Pausing after a question to allow students time to think"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Waiting for the bell to end class"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Delaying tests until students are ready"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Pausing after a question to allow students time to think.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','Principles of Teaching','hard','Which is an example of authentic assessment?','[{"key": "A", "text": "Multiple choice exam"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Fill-in-the-blank test"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Science fair project demonstrating real-world application"}, {"key": "D", "text": "True-or-false quiz"}]','C','The correct answer is C. Science fair project demonstrating real-world application.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','Principles of Teaching','hard','Competency-based education focuses on:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Covering all chapters in the textbook"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Students demonstrating mastery of specific skills"}, {"key": "C", "text": "The teacher''s lecture time"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Standardized test preparation"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Students demonstrating mastery of specific skills.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','The Teaching Profession','hard','A teacher who shares test questions with parents before the exam is committing:','[{"key": "A", "text": "A kind gesture"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Academic dishonesty and a violation of professional ethics"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Good parent-teacher relations"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Transparency"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Academic dishonesty and a violation of professional ethics.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','The Teaching Profession','hard','The ''Oath of Allegiance'' taken by teachers upon PRC registration means:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Loyalty to the school principal"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Loyalty to the Philippines and commitment to professional duties"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Loyalty to the DepEd Secretary"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Loyalty to the community only"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Loyalty to the Philippines and commitment to professional duties.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','The Teaching Profession','hard','A teacher being bullied by colleagues should FIRST:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Resign immediately"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Report to the school head through proper grievance procedures"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Retaliate"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Ignore the situation completely"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Report to the school head through proper grievance procedures.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','The Teaching Profession','hard','RA 10533 is known as the:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Anti-Bullying Act"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Enhanced Basic Education Act (K to 12 Law)"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Data Privacy Act"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Magna Carta for Teachers"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Enhanced Basic Education Act (K to 12 Law).','elementary'),
('Professional Education','The Teaching Profession','hard','''Academic integrity'' is BEST described as:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Getting high grades at all costs"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Honesty and ethical behavior in all academic work"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Memorizing facts perfectly"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Submitting work on time"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Honesty and ethical behavior in all academic work.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','The Teaching Profession','hard','The ''Child Protection Policy'' in schools is guided by:','[{"key": "A", "text": "DepEd Order No. 40, s. 2012"}, {"key": "B", "text": "RA 7836"}, {"key": "C", "text": "RA 4670"}, {"key": "D", "text": "RA 8981"}]','A','The correct answer is A. DepEd Order No. 40, s. 2012.','elementary'),
('General Education','English','easy','The commonly heard phrase ''I could care less'' is:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Grammatically correct and meaningful"}, {"key": "B", "text": "A common error \u2014 the correct phrase is ''I couldn''t care less''"}, {"key": "C", "text": "An example of personification"}, {"key": "D", "text": "An idiom meaning you care a lot"}]','B','The correct answer is B. A common error — the correct phrase is ''I couldn''t care less''.','elementary'),
('General Education','English','easy','The word ''magnanimous'' means:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Very large"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Very generous and forgiving"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Extremely angry"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Highly magnetic"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Very generous and forgiving.','elementary'),
('General Education','English','easy','Which sentence correctly uses ''whom''?','[{"key": "A", "text": "Who did you speak to?"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Whom called the office?"}, {"key": "C", "text": "To whom should I address this letter?"}, {"key": "D", "text": "The student who I helped passed."}]','C','The correct answer is C. To whom should I address this letter?.','elementary'),
('General Education','English','easy','An oxymoron combines:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Extreme exaggeration"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Two contradictory terms (e.g., ''deafening silence'')"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Human qualities given to non-human things"}, {"key": "D", "text": "A comparison using ''like'' or ''as''"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Two contradictory terms (e.g., ''deafening silence'').','elementary'),
('General Education','English','easy','Which sentence contains a misplaced modifier?','[{"key": "A", "text": "The child ate the cake happily."}, {"key": "B", "text": "She returned the book to the library that was overdue."}, {"key": "C", "text": "The teacher graded the tests carefully."}, {"key": "D", "text": "He finished his homework before dinner."}]','B','The correct answer is B. She returned the book to the library that was overdue..','elementary'),
('General Education','English','easy','The word ''ameliorate'' means:','[{"key": "A", "text": "To make worse"}, {"key": "B", "text": "To improve a bad situation"}, {"key": "C", "text": "To destroy completely"}, {"key": "D", "text": "To remember clearly"}]','B','The correct answer is B. To improve a bad situation.','elementary'),
('General Education','English','easy','Which word has the most NEGATIVE connotation?','[{"key": "A", "text": "Frugal"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Thrifty"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Economical"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Cheap"}]','D','The correct answer is D. Cheap.','elementary'),
('General Education','English','easy','A ''prologue'' in literature comes:','[{"key": "A", "text": "At the end of a story"}, {"key": "B", "text": "At the beginning, setting up the story"}, {"key": "C", "text": "In the middle of the plot"}, {"key": "D", "text": "After the conclusion"}]','B','The correct answer is B. At the beginning, setting up the story.','elementary'),
('General Education','Mathematics','medium','If the average of 5 numbers is 12, what is their sum?','[{"key": "A", "text": "50"}, {"key": "B", "text": "55"}, {"key": "C", "text": "60"}, {"key": "D", "text": "65"}]','C','The correct answer is C. 60.','elementary'),
('General Education','Mathematics','medium','A water tank is 3/4 full and contains 450 liters. What is its full capacity?','[{"key": "A", "text": "500 L"}, {"key": "B", "text": "550 L"}, {"key": "C", "text": "600 L"}, {"key": "D", "text": "650 L"}]','C','The correct answer is C. 600 L.','elementary'),
('General Education','Mathematics','medium','The ratio of passing to failing students is 4:1. If 40 passed, how many failed?','[{"key": "A", "text": "8"}, {"key": "B", "text": "10"}, {"key": "C", "text": "12"}, {"key": "D", "text": "15"}]','B','The correct answer is B. 10.','elementary'),
('General Education','Mathematics','medium','The supplement of a 65° angle is:','[{"key": "A", "text": "25\u00b0"}, {"key": "B", "text": "35\u00b0"}, {"key": "C", "text": "115\u00b0"}, {"key": "D", "text": "125\u00b0"}]','C','The correct answer is C. 115°.','elementary'),
('General Education','Mathematics','medium','Express 5/8 as a percentage:','[{"key": "A", "text": "58%"}, {"key": "B", "text": "60%"}, {"key": "C", "text": "62.5%"}, {"key": "D", "text": "65%"}]','C','The correct answer is C. 62.5%.','elementary'),
('General Education','Mathematics','medium','Arithmetic sequence: 5, 11, 17, 23, ___. Find the next term.','[{"key": "A", "text": "27"}, {"key": "B", "text": "29"}, {"key": "C", "text": "31"}, {"key": "D", "text": "33"}]','B','The correct answer is B. 29.','elementary'),
('General Education','Mathematics','medium','The product of two negative integers is always:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Negative"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Positive"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Zero"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Undefined"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Positive.','elementary'),
('General Education','Science','medium','The speed of light is approximately:','[{"key": "A", "text": "300,000 km/s"}, {"key": "B", "text": "300,000 m/s"}, {"key": "C", "text": "30,000 km/s"}, {"key": "D", "text": "3,000 km/s"}]','A','The correct answer is A. 300,000 km/s.','elementary'),
('General Education','Science','medium','The organelle known as the ''powerhouse of the cell'' is the:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Nucleus"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Ribosome"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Mitochondria"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Vacuole"}]','C','The correct answer is C. Mitochondria.','elementary'),
('General Education','Science','medium','Acid rain is primarily caused by:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Excess carbon dioxide"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Sulfur dioxide and nitrogen oxides mixing with water vapor"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Ozone depletion"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Volcanic ash"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Sulfur dioxide and nitrogen oxides mixing with water vapor.','elementary'),
('General Education','Science','medium','The Law of Conservation of Energy states that energy:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Can be created from nothing"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Can be destroyed"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Cannot be created or destroyed, only transformed"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Is always lost in conversions"}]','C','The correct answer is C. Cannot be created or destroyed, only transformed.','elementary'),
('General Education','Science','medium','Which type of wave REQUIRES a medium to travel through?','[{"key": "A", "text": "Light waves"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Radio waves"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Sound waves"}, {"key": "D", "text": "X-rays"}]','C','The correct answer is C. Sound waves.','elementary'),
('General Education','Science','medium','The process of changing a solid directly to a gas (without passing through liquid) is:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Evaporation"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Condensation"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Sublimation"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Melting"}]','C','The correct answer is C. Sublimation.','elementary'),
('General Education','Science','medium','In human reproduction, fertilization of an egg by sperm occurs in the:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Uterus"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Ovary"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Fallopian tube"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Cervix"}]','C','The correct answer is C. Fallopian tube.','elementary'),
('General Education','Social Studies','medium','The ''Cavite Mutiny'' (1872) led to the execution of:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Jose Rizal, Marcelo del Pilar, and Graciano Lopez Jaena"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Fathers Gomez, Burgos, and Zamora (GomBurZa)"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Andres Bonifacio and Emilio Jacinto"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Apolinario Mabini and Antonio Luna"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Fathers Gomez, Burgos, and Zamora (GomBurZa).','elementary'),
('General Education','Social Studies','medium','Jose Rizal''s ''Noli Me Tangere'':','[{"key": "A", "text": "Celebrates Spanish rule"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Exposes social injustices and abuses during Spanish colonization"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Describes Philippine beauty"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Tells the story of the Katipunan"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Exposes social injustices and abuses during Spanish colonization.','elementary'),
('General Education','Social Studies','medium','The Cordillera Administrative Region is located in:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Visayas"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Mindanao"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Northern Luzon"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Southern Luzon"}]','C','The correct answer is C. Northern Luzon.','elementary'),
('General Education','Social Studies','medium','''Pasalubong'' refers to:','[{"key": "A", "text": "A farewell gift"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Bringing gifts or souvenirs when returning from a trip"}, {"key": "C", "text": "A birthday celebration"}, {"key": "D", "text": "A religious offering"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Bringing gifts or souvenirs when returning from a trip.','elementary'),
('General Education','Social Studies','medium','The Renaissance cultural movement began in:','[{"key": "A", "text": "England"}, {"key": "B", "text": "France"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Italy"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Germany"}]','C','The correct answer is C. Italy.','elementary'),
('General Education','Social Studies','medium','The Supreme Court of the Philippines is composed of how many justices?','[{"key": "A", "text": "9"}, {"key": "B", "text": "12"}, {"key": "C", "text": "15"}, {"key": "D", "text": "17"}]','C','The correct answer is C. 15.','elementary'),
('General Education','Social Studies','medium','''Opportunity cost'' in economics means:','[{"key": "A", "text": "The cost of all available options"}, {"key": "B", "text": "The value of the next best alternative forgone"}, {"key": "C", "text": "The total cost of production"}, {"key": "D", "text": "A tax paid on business opportunities"}]','B','The correct answer is B. The value of the next best alternative forgone.','elementary'),
('General Education','Social Studies','medium','The Philippine flag''s blue stripe represents:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Peace and tranquility"}, {"key": "B", "text": "The sky and seas"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Peace, truth, and justice"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Valor and courage"}]','C','The correct answer is C. Peace, truth, and justice.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','Child and Adolescent Development','medium','According to Piaget, ''object permanence'' is achieved during the:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Preoperational stage"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Sensorimotor stage"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Concrete Operational stage"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Formal Operational stage"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Sensorimotor stage.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','Child and Adolescent Development','medium','Bloom''s Taxonomy was revised in 2001. The most significant change was:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Analysis was removed"}, {"key": "B", "text": "''Synthesis'' was renamed ''Creating'' and moved to the highest level"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Evaluation was removed"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Knowledge was split into two levels"}]','B','The correct answer is B. ''Synthesis'' was renamed ''Creating'' and moved to the highest level.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','Child and Adolescent Development','medium','In Erikson''s ''Industry vs. Inferiority'' stage, a child who succeeds develops:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Trust"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Autonomy"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Competence and confidence"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Identity"}]','C','The correct answer is C. Competence and confidence.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','Child and Adolescent Development','medium','The ABC model in behavior management stands for:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Ability, Behavior, Consequences"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Antecedent, Behavior, Consequence"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Attitude, Behavior, Change"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Awareness, Building, Community"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Antecedent, Behavior, Consequence.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','Child and Adolescent Development','medium','Maslow''s ''Belongingness and Love'' needs include:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Food and water"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Physical safety"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Friendships, family bonds, and social acceptance"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Self-respect and achievement"}]','C','The correct answer is C. Friendships, family bonds, and social acceptance.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','Child and Adolescent Development','medium','''Transfer of learning'' occurs when:','[{"key": "A", "text": "A student moves to a new school"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Skills learned in one context are applied in a different context"}, {"key": "C", "text": "A teacher transfers between schools"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Students share notes with each other"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Skills learned in one context are applied in a different context.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','Child and Adolescent Development','medium','The interactionist view of language development holds that:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Language is entirely innate"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Language develops only through reinforcement"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Language acquisition involves both biological readiness and social experience"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Language is purely social"}]','C','The correct answer is C. Language acquisition involves both biological readiness and social experience.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','Principles of Teaching','medium','Inductive teaching moves from:','[{"key": "A", "text": "General principles to specific examples"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Specific examples to general principles"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Abstract to concrete"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Old knowledge to new knowledge"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Specific examples to general principles.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','Principles of Teaching','medium','Students designing and conducting their own science experiment is an example of:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Memorizing elements"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Inquiry-based learning"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Copying notes from the board"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Listening to a lecture"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Inquiry-based learning.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','Principles of Teaching','medium','A ''diagnostic test'' in teaching is used to:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Test the teacher''s knowledge"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Identify students'' prior knowledge and learning gaps BEFORE instruction"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Give final grades"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Compare student performance"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Identify students'' prior knowledge and learning gaps BEFORE instruction.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','Principles of Teaching','hard','''Looping'' in education refers to:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Using circular seating arrangements"}, {"key": "B", "text": "A teacher staying with the same group of students for more than one year"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Repeating lessons many times"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Reviewing old lessons"}]','B','The correct answer is B. A teacher staying with the same group of students for more than one year.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','Principles of Teaching','hard','A teacher giving immediate, specific feedback after each student response is applying:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Summative assessment"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Constructive feedback and formative assessment"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Standardized testing"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Portfolio evaluation"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Constructive feedback and formative assessment.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','Principles of Teaching','hard','Which of the following is an affective learning objective?','[{"key": "A", "text": "List 5 properties of metals."}, {"key": "B", "text": "Solve quadratic equations."}, {"key": "C", "text": "Demonstrate respect for classmates'' opinions."}, {"key": "D", "text": "Write a 5-paragraph essay."}]','C','The correct answer is C. Demonstrate respect for classmates'' opinions..','elementary'),
('Professional Education','Principles of Teaching','hard','The ''flipped classroom'' model means:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Rearranging classroom furniture"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Students learn new content at home (via videos/readings) and apply/practice in class"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Teachers prepare all materials at home"}, {"key": "D", "text": "The class schedule is reversed"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Students learn new content at home (via videos/readings) and apply/practice in class.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','The Teaching Profession','hard','A teacher who copies textbook content without permission is violating:','[{"key": "A", "text": "School policy only"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Intellectual Property Rights / Copyright Law"}, {"key": "C", "text": "RA 7836"}, {"key": "D", "text": "RA 4670"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Intellectual Property Rights / Copyright Law.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','The Teaching Profession','hard','The ''Data Privacy Act'' (RA 10173) protects:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Teacher salary information"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Personal data and information of individuals"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Student test results only"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Government records"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Personal data and information of individuals.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','The Teaching Profession','hard','Which principle requires a teacher to avoid ALL forms of bias in evaluation?','[{"key": "A", "text": "Principle of honesty"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Principle of impartiality / objectivity"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Principle of confidentiality"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Principle of accountability"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Principle of impartiality / objectivity.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','The Teaching Profession','hard','Under RA 4670, teachers are entitled to:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Free housing from the government"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Study leave with pay to pursue graduate studies"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Free tuition for their children"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Government car service"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Study leave with pay to pursue graduate studies.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','The Teaching Profession','hard','A teacher who violates the Code of Ethics may face:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Criminal charges only"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Suspension or revocation of PRC license after due process"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Immediate dismissal without due process"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Only a verbal warning"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Suspension or revocation of PRC license after due process.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','The Teaching Profession','hard','The Anti-Bullying Act of 2013 is:','[{"key": "A", "text": "RA 10175"}, {"key": "B", "text": "RA 10627"}, {"key": "C", "text": "RA 10533"}, {"key": "D", "text": "RA 10173"}]','B','The correct answer is B. RA 10627.','elementary'),
('General Education','English','easy','Which is a correctly written first conditional sentence?','[{"key": "A", "text": "If she studies hard, she would pass."}, {"key": "B", "text": "If she studies hard, she will pass."}, {"key": "C", "text": "If she will study hard, she will pass."}, {"key": "D", "text": "If she studied hard, she will pass."}]','B','The correct answer is B. If she studies hard, she will pass..','elementary'),
('General Education','English','easy','The word ''gregarious'' means:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Shy and withdrawn"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Fond of company; sociable"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Extremely intelligent"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Very aggressive"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Fond of company; sociable.','elementary'),
('General Education','English','easy','Which is an example of alliteration?','[{"key": "A", "text": "The moon shines bright."}, {"key": "B", "text": "Peter Piper picked a peck of pickled peppers."}, {"key": "C", "text": "Life is a river."}, {"key": "D", "text": "The cat meowed loudly."}]','B','The correct answer is B. Peter Piper picked a peck of pickled peppers..','elementary'),
('General Education','English','easy','A word with the same spelling but different meanings (e.g., ''bank'') is called a:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Synonym"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Antonym"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Homonym (homograph)"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Euphemism"}]','C','The correct answer is C. Homonym (homograph).','elementary'),
('General Education','English','easy','Which sentence uses parallel structure correctly?','[{"key": "A", "text": "She likes swimming, to run, and hiking."}, {"key": "B", "text": "She likes swimming, running, and hiking."}, {"key": "C", "text": "She likes to swim, running, and hiking."}, {"key": "D", "text": "She likes swimming, to run, and to hike only on weekends."}]','B','The correct answer is B. She likes swimming, running, and hiking..','elementary'),
('General Education','English','easy','An ''epilogue'' in literature:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Introduces the characters"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Occurs before the main story"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Comes AFTER the main story to conclude or reflect"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Describes the setting in detail"}]','C','The correct answer is C. Comes AFTER the main story to conclude or reflect.','elementary'),
('General Education','English','easy','The word ''benign'' means:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Dangerous and harmful"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Gentle, kind, or not harmful"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Very dark"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Extremely fast"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Gentle, kind, or not harmful.','elementary'),
('General Education','English','easy','Which sentence correctly uses ''fewer''?','[{"key": "A", "text": "We have fewer time today."}, {"key": "B", "text": "There are fewer books on the shelf."}, {"key": "C", "text": "She has fewer patience."}, {"key": "D", "text": "I have fewer money."}]','B','The correct answer is B. There are fewer books on the shelf..','elementary'),
('General Education','Mathematics','medium','The decimal 0.125 is equal to which fraction?','[{"key": "A", "text": "1/8"}, {"key": "B", "text": "1/6"}, {"key": "C", "text": "1/4"}, {"key": "D", "text": "1/5"}]','A','The correct answer is A. 1/8.','elementary'),
('General Education','Mathematics','medium','If the perimeter of a square is 48 cm, what is its area?','[{"key": "A", "text": "96 cm\u00b2"}, {"key": "B", "text": "100 cm\u00b2"}, {"key": "C", "text": "144 cm\u00b2"}, {"key": "D", "text": "120 cm\u00b2"}]','C','The correct answer is C. 144 cm².','elementary'),
('General Education','Mathematics','medium','In a class of 40 students, 25% scored 90 or above. How many students is that?','[{"key": "A", "text": "8"}, {"key": "B", "text": "10"}, {"key": "C", "text": "12"}, {"key": "D", "text": "15"}]','B','The correct answer is B. 10.','elementary'),
('General Education','Mathematics','medium','Solve: 3x + 7 = 22','[{"key": "A", "text": "x = 3"}, {"key": "B", "text": "x = 4"}, {"key": "C", "text": "x = 5"}, {"key": "D", "text": "x = 6"}]','C','The correct answer is C. x = 5.','elementary'),
('General Education','Mathematics','medium','What is 7% of 300?','[{"key": "A", "text": "19"}, {"key": "B", "text": "21"}, {"key": "C", "text": "23"}, {"key": "D", "text": "25"}]','B','The correct answer is B. 21.','elementary'),
('General Education','Mathematics','medium','Buses depart every 15 minutes starting at 6:00 AM. How many buses depart BEFORE 8:00 AM?','[{"key": "A", "text": "7"}, {"key": "B", "text": "8"}, {"key": "C", "text": "9"}, {"key": "D", "text": "10"}]','B','The correct answer is B. 8.','elementary'),
('General Education','Mathematics','medium','Which number is NOT a factor of 36?','[{"key": "A", "text": "4"}, {"key": "B", "text": "9"}, {"key": "C", "text": "12"}, {"key": "D", "text": "8"}]','D','The correct answer is D. 8.','elementary'),
('General Education','Science','medium','Which scientist formulated the theory of evolution by natural selection?','[{"key": "A", "text": "Louis Pasteur"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Charles Darwin"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Gregor Mendel"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Albert Einstein"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Charles Darwin.','elementary'),
('General Education','Science','medium','Vaccines work by:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Killing bacteria directly"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Stimulating the immune system to recognize and fight specific pathogens"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Reducing fever"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Providing nutrients to fight infection"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Stimulating the immune system to recognize and fight specific pathogens.','elementary'),
('General Education','Science','medium','Which of the following is a fossil fuel?','[{"key": "A", "text": "Hydropower"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Wind energy"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Coal"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Solar energy"}]','C','The correct answer is C. Coal.','elementary'),
('General Education','Science','medium','The SI unit of force is:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Watt"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Joule"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Newton"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Pascal"}]','C','The correct answer is C. Newton.','elementary'),
('General Education','Science','medium','Earthquake magnitude is commonly measured using the:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Beaufort scale"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Richter scale"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Mercalli scale"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Kelvin scale"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Richter scale.','elementary'),
('General Education','Science','medium','Which of the following is NOT a property of metals?','[{"key": "A", "text": "Conductivity of heat"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Conductivity of electricity"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Brittleness"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Luster"}]','C','The correct answer is C. Brittleness.','elementary'),
('General Education','Science','medium','The best method to separate salt from seawater is:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Filtration"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Evaporation / distillation"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Magnetic separation"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Decantation"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Evaporation / distillation.','elementary'),
('General Education','Social Studies','medium','The ''Balangiga Massacre'' occurred during the:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Spanish colonial period"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Philippine-American War"}, {"key": "C", "text": "World War II"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Japanese Occupation"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Philippine-American War.','elementary'),
('General Education','Social Studies','medium','Andres Bonifacio is known as the:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Brains of the Revolution"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Great Plebeian"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Father of the Filipino Nation"}, {"key": "D", "text": "First President"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Great Plebeian.','elementary'),
('General Education','Social Studies','medium','The Chocolate Hills are located in:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Cebu"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Bohol"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Leyte"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Samar"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Bohol.','elementary'),
('General Education','Social Studies','medium','''Pagpapahalaga sa pamilya'' refers to:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Respect for nature"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Strong family orientation \u2014 placing great importance on family"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Respect for authority"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Hospitality to guests"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Strong family orientation — placing great importance on family.','elementary'),
('General Education','Social Studies','medium','The Marshall Plan (1948) was aimed at:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Rebuilding Europe after WWII with American aid"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Creating NATO"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Establishing the United Nations"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Controlling the Soviet Union militarily"}]','A','The correct answer is A. Rebuilding Europe after WWII with American aid.','elementary'),
('General Education','Social Studies','medium','The power to declare war in the Philippines belongs to:','[{"key": "A", "text": "The President alone"}, {"key": "B", "text": "The Supreme Court"}, {"key": "C", "text": "The Congress"}, {"key": "D", "text": "The Armed Forces"}]','C','The correct answer is C. The Congress.','elementary'),
('General Education','Social Studies','medium','''Comparative advantage'' in economics means:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Producing more than other countries"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Producing a good at a lower opportunity cost than others"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Having superior technology"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Trading only with allied nations"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Producing a good at a lower opportunity cost than others.','elementary'),
('General Education','Social Studies','medium','APEC (Asia-Pacific Economic Cooperation) is:','[{"key": "A", "text": "A military alliance"}, {"key": "B", "text": "An economic forum for Pacific Rim nations"}, {"key": "C", "text": "A United Nations body"}, {"key": "D", "text": "A Southeast Asian organization only"}]','B','The correct answer is B. An economic forum for Pacific Rim nations.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','Child and Adolescent Development','medium','Which stage comes SECOND in Piaget''s theory?','[{"key": "A", "text": "Sensorimotor"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Preoperational"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Concrete Operational"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Formal Operational"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Preoperational.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','Child and Adolescent Development','medium','''Private speech'' (talking to oneself) in Vygotsky''s theory is:','[{"key": "A", "text": "A sign of developmental delay"}, {"key": "B", "text": "A cognitive tool children use to guide their own behavior"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Meaningless chatter"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Evidence of poor social skills"}]','B','The correct answer is B. A cognitive tool children use to guide their own behavior.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','Child and Adolescent Development','medium','Which Bloom''s level requires students to JUDGE the value of something?','[{"key": "A", "text": "Apply"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Analyze"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Evaluate"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Create"}]','C','The correct answer is C. Evaluate.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','Child and Adolescent Development','medium','Erikson''s ''Generativity vs. Stagnation'' stage occurs during:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Adolescence"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Early adulthood"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Middle adulthood"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Late adulthood"}]','C','The correct answer is C. Middle adulthood.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','Child and Adolescent Development','medium','''Learned helplessness'' means:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Students who have been taught to help others"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Repeated failure causes a person to stop trying"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Students who depend on teachers too much"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Students who refuse to work independently"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Repeated failure causes a person to stop trying.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','Child and Adolescent Development','medium','John Dewey''s philosophy of education emphasizes:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Rote memorization"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Learning by doing and experience-based education"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Teacher-centered instruction"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Strict discipline"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Learning by doing and experience-based education.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','Child and Adolescent Development','medium','Gardner''s ''Interpersonal Intelligence'' refers to the ability to:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Understand oneself deeply"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Understand and interact effectively with others"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Perform music"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Reason spatially"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Understand and interact effectively with others.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','Principles of Teaching','medium','A teacher who modifies instruction based on students'' quiz results is practicing:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Rigid lesson planning"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Data-driven / responsive teaching"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Teaching to the test"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Standardized instruction"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Data-driven / responsive teaching.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','Principles of Teaching','medium','In the ''Jigsaw'' cooperative learning strategy:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Students compete against each other"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Each student becomes an expert on one part and teaches it to peers"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Students work alone on puzzles"}, {"key": "D", "text": "The teacher explains everything piece by piece"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Each student becomes an expert on one part and teaches it to peers.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','Principles of Teaching','medium','A placement test is given to students:','[{"key": "A", "text": "At the end of the school year"}, {"key": "B", "text": "At the start of a program to determine appropriate level or group"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Monthly to track progress"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Only to failing students"}]','B','The correct answer is B. At the start of a program to determine appropriate level or group.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','Principles of Teaching','hard','A lesson where the teacher shows examples first and asks students to identify the pattern is:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Deductive teaching"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Inductive teaching"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Direct instruction"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Expository teaching"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Inductive teaching.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','Principles of Teaching','hard','Which classroom arrangement is BEST for a lecture-style lesson?','[{"key": "A", "text": "U-shape"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Cluster / group arrangement"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Traditional rows"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Circle"}]','C','The correct answer is C. Traditional rows.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','Principles of Teaching','hard','An IEP (Individualized Education Plan) is designed for:','[{"key": "A", "text": "High-achieving students"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Students with special educational needs"}, {"key": "C", "text": "All students equally"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Teachers'' professional development"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Students with special educational needs.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','Principles of Teaching','hard','The ''anticipatory set'' in Madeline Hunter''s lesson plan model is the:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Homework assignment"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Hook / motivational activity that prepares students for learning"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Assessment portion"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Lesson closure"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Hook / motivational activity that prepares students for learning.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','The Teaching Profession','hard','A teacher who receives an anonymous complaint should:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Ignore it completely"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Investigate with professionalism and due process"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Retaliate against suspected complainants"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Dismiss it as baseless"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Investigate with professionalism and due process.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','The Teaching Profession','hard','The ''Anti-Sexual Harassment Act'' in the Philippines is:','[{"key": "A", "text": "RA 7877"}, {"key": "B", "text": "RA 7836"}, {"key": "C", "text": "RA 10627"}, {"key": "D", "text": "RA 9262"}]','A','The correct answer is A. RA 7877.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','The Teaching Profession','hard','Professional teachers who fail to renew their PRC ID are:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Automatically dismissed"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Still considered professionals but need to comply with renewal requirements"}, {"key": "C", "text": "No longer allowed to teach"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Referred to DepEd for disciplinary action"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Still considered professionals but need to comply with renewal requirements.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','The Teaching Profession','hard','A student who consistently fails should FIRST be:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Retained in the same grade automatically"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Given additional support, remedial instruction, and a parent conference"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Excluded from the classroom"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Referred to DepEd central office"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Given additional support, remedial instruction, and a parent conference.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','The Teaching Profession','hard','''Due process'' in school disciplinary cases means:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Punishing students immediately"}, {"key": "B", "text": "The student has the right to be heard and informed of charges before punishment"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Only the principal decides disciplinary action"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Parents are always the final decision-makers"}]','B','The correct answer is B. The student has the right to be heard and informed of charges before punishment.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','The Teaching Profession','hard','Teachers who engage in illegal activities may have their PRC license:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Only suspended temporarily"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Revoked by the PRC after due process"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Transferred to another region"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Automatically renewed after 5 years"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Revoked by the PRC after due process.','elementary'),
('General Education','English','easy','Which of the following is a complex sentence?','[{"key": "A", "text": "She runs and she sings."}, {"key": "B", "text": "She runs, but she doesn''t sing."}, {"key": "C", "text": "Because she runs every day, she is healthy."}, {"key": "D", "text": "She runs. She sings."}]','C','The correct answer is C. Because she runs every day, she is healthy..','elementary'),
('General Education','English','easy','The word ''melancholy'' means:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Joyful and happy"}, {"key": "B", "text": "A feeling of sadness or depression"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Extremely angry"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Very energetic"}]','B','The correct answer is B. A feeling of sadness or depression.','elementary'),
('General Education','English','easy','Which sentence uses ''effect'' correctly?','[{"key": "A", "text": "The storm will effect our travel plans."}, {"key": "B", "text": "The new law has had a positive affect on the economy."}, {"key": "C", "text": "The effect of the new policy was felt immediately."}, {"key": "D", "text": "She was effected by the news."}]','C','The correct answer is C. The effect of the new policy was felt immediately..','elementary'),
('General Education','English','easy','The literary term ''antagonist'' refers to:','[{"key": "A", "text": "The main character"}, {"key": "B", "text": "The character who opposes the protagonist"}, {"key": "C", "text": "The narrator of the story"}, {"key": "D", "text": "The wisest character"}]','B','The correct answer is B. The character who opposes the protagonist.','elementary'),
('General Education','English','easy','''Every cloud has a silver lining'' is an example of a:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Hyperbole"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Proverb"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Simile"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Paradox"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Proverb.','elementary'),
('General Education','English','easy','A word that imitates the sound it describes (e.g., ''sizzle'', ''buzz'') is called:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Alliteration"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Assonance"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Onomatopoeia"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Consonance"}]','C','The correct answer is C. Onomatopoeia.','elementary'),
('General Education','English','easy','The ''rising action'' in a story refers to:','[{"key": "A", "text": "The highest point of tension"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Events building up toward the climax"}, {"key": "C", "text": "The resolution of the story"}, {"key": "D", "text": "The introduction of characters"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Events building up toward the climax.','elementary'),
('General Education','English','easy','Which sentence uses parentheses correctly?','[{"key": "A", "text": "(She) went to the store."}, {"key": "B", "text": "She went to the store (the one on Rizal Street)."}, {"key": "C", "text": "She (went) to the store."}, {"key": "D", "text": "She went (to the) store."}]','B','The correct answer is B. She went to the store (the one on Rizal Street)..','elementary'),
('General Education','Mathematics','medium','What is the GCF (HCF) of 36 and 48?','[{"key": "A", "text": "6"}, {"key": "B", "text": "8"}, {"key": "C", "text": "12"}, {"key": "D", "text": "24"}]','C','The correct answer is C. 12.','elementary'),
('General Education','Mathematics','medium','A rectangle''s length is twice its width. If the perimeter is 60 cm, what is the width?','[{"key": "A", "text": "8 cm"}, {"key": "B", "text": "10 cm"}, {"key": "C", "text": "12 cm"}, {"key": "D", "text": "15 cm"}]','B','The correct answer is B. 10 cm.','elementary'),
('General Education','Mathematics','medium','Which number is divisible by 6?','[{"key": "A", "text": "125"}, {"key": "B", "text": "144"}, {"key": "C", "text": "200"}, {"key": "D", "text": "256"}]','B','The correct answer is B. 144.','elementary'),
('General Education','Mathematics','medium','The value of π (pi) is approximately:','[{"key": "A", "text": "3.12"}, {"key": "B", "text": "3.14"}, {"key": "C", "text": "3.16"}, {"key": "D", "text": "3.18"}]','B','The correct answer is B. 3.14.','elementary'),
('General Education','Mathematics','medium','Find the missing number: 8, 16, ___, 64, 128','[{"key": "A", "text": "24"}, {"key": "B", "text": "32"}, {"key": "C", "text": "40"}, {"key": "D", "text": "48"}]','B','The correct answer is B. 32.','elementary'),
('General Education','Mathematics','medium','A school has 480 students; 5/8 are girls. How many are boys?','[{"key": "A", "text": "160"}, {"key": "B", "text": "180"}, {"key": "C", "text": "200"}, {"key": "D", "text": "240"}]','B','The correct answer is B. 180.','elementary'),
('General Education','Mathematics','medium','Evaluate: 15 − 3 × (4 − 1)','[{"key": "A", "text": "6"}, {"key": "B", "text": "9"}, {"key": "C", "text": "12"}, {"key": "D", "text": "36"}]','A','The correct answer is A. 6.','elementary'),
('General Education','Science','medium','The correct order of the human digestive process is:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Stomach \u2192 Mouth \u2192 Small intestine \u2192 Large intestine"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Mouth \u2192 Esophagus \u2192 Stomach \u2192 Small intestine \u2192 Large intestine"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Mouth \u2192 Stomach \u2192 Esophagus \u2192 Small intestine \u2192 Large intestine"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Esophagus \u2192 Mouth \u2192 Stomach \u2192 Large intestine \u2192 Small intestine"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Mouth → Esophagus → Stomach → Small intestine → Large intestine.','elementary'),
('General Education','Science','medium','Renewable energy resources include:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Coal and natural gas"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Petroleum and nuclear"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Wind, solar, and geothermal"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Coal, oil, and solar"}]','C','The correct answer is C. Wind, solar, and geothermal.','elementary'),
('General Education','Science','medium','A solution with pH less than 7 is classified as:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Neutral"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Basic / alkaline"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Acidic"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Salty"}]','C','The correct answer is C. Acidic.','elementary'),
('General Education','Science','medium','The Earth''s ROTATION causes:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Seasons"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Day and night"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Ocean tides"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Eclipses"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Day and night.','elementary'),
('General Education','Science','medium','Which is an example of Newton''s Third Law?','[{"key": "A", "text": "A ball rolling to a stop due to friction"}, {"key": "B", "text": "A rocket pushing gas downward and being propelled upward"}, {"key": "C", "text": "A falling apple accelerating due to gravity"}, {"key": "D", "text": "A car accelerating when the engine applies force"}]','B','The correct answer is B. A rocket pushing gas downward and being propelled upward.','elementary'),
('General Education','Science','medium','The function of red blood cells is to:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Fight infection"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Carry oxygen throughout the body"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Clot wounds"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Digest food"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Carry oxygen throughout the body.','elementary'),
('General Education','Science','medium','Global warming is primarily caused by:','[{"key": "A", "text": "The hole in the ozone layer"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Increased greenhouse gases (CO\u2082, methane) in the atmosphere"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Deforestation only"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Nuclear power plants"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Increased greenhouse gases (CO₂, methane) in the atmosphere.','elementary'),
('General Education','Social Studies','medium','The Philippine Congress is bicameral, meaning it has:','[{"key": "A", "text": "One chamber"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Two chambers: Senate and House of Representatives"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Three chambers"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Regional assemblies only"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Two chambers: Senate and House of Representatives.','elementary'),
('General Education','Social Studies','medium','The ''Ilustrados'' in Philippine history were:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Illiterate farmers"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Educated Filipinos who advocated for reforms during Spanish colonization"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Spanish missionaries"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Members of the Katipunan"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Educated Filipinos who advocated for reforms during Spanish colonization.','elementary'),
('General Education','Social Studies','medium','The Philippines'' land borders with neighboring countries:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Malaysia"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Indonesia"}, {"key": "C", "text": "None \u2014 it is an archipelago with no land borders"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Papua New Guinea"}]','C','The correct answer is C. None — it is an archipelago with no land borders.','elementary'),
('General Education','Social Studies','medium','''Hiya'' (shame) in Filipino culture often causes individuals to:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Speak up for themselves"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Avoid actions that could bring embarrassment or loss of face"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Show aggression"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Ignore social norms"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Avoid actions that could bring embarrassment or loss of face.','elementary'),
('General Education','Social Studies','medium','The Korean War (1950–1953) was a conflict between:','[{"key": "A", "text": "North Korea (Soviet-backed) and South Korea (UN-backed)"}, {"key": "B", "text": "China and Japan"}, {"key": "C", "text": "The United States and China only"}, {"key": "D", "text": "North Korea and Japan"}]','A','The correct answer is A. North Korea (Soviet-backed) and South Korea (UN-backed).','elementary'),
('General Education','Social Studies','medium','''Habeas corpus'' is a legal term that means:','[{"key": "A", "text": "The right to bear arms"}, {"key": "B", "text": "You shall have the body \u2014 protecting against unlawful detention"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Guilty until proven innocent"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Freedom of speech"}]','B','The correct answer is B. You shall have the body — protecting against unlawful detention.','elementary'),
('General Education','Social Studies','medium','A ''budget deficit'' occurs when:','[{"key": "A", "text": "A government earns more than it spends"}, {"key": "B", "text": "A government spends more than its revenue"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Trade is balanced"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Taxes are reduced"}]','B','The correct answer is B. A government spends more than its revenue.','elementary'),
('General Education','Social Studies','medium','''Separation of church and state'' in the Philippines means:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Religious persons cannot vote"}, {"key": "B", "text": "The government does not establish or favor any religion"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Churches cannot be built near schools"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Religion cannot be taught anywhere"}]','B','The correct answer is B. The government does not establish or favor any religion.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','Child and Adolescent Development','medium','Piaget''s ''conservation'' refers to a child''s ability to understand that:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Environmental conservation is important"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Quantity remains the same despite changes in shape or appearance"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Memories are stored permanently"}, {"key": "D", "text": "One can focus on only one task at a time"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Quantity remains the same despite changes in shape or appearance.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','Child and Adolescent Development','medium','The ''Language Acquisition Device'' (LAD) theory was proposed by:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Vygotsky"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Piaget"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Noam Chomsky"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Skinner"}]','C','The correct answer is C. Noam Chomsky.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','Child and Adolescent Development','medium','The affective domain''s lowest level (''Receiving'') means:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Reacting with strong emotion"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Being willing to listen and pay attention to stimuli"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Actively seeking out new values"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Internalizing values as part of identity"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Being willing to listen and pay attention to stimuli.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','Child and Adolescent Development','medium','Erikson''s ''Identity vs. Role Confusion'' stage occurs during:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Early childhood"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Middle childhood"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Adolescence"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Early adulthood"}]','C','The correct answer is C. Adolescence.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','Child and Adolescent Development','medium','''Extinction'' in behavior modification means a behavior weakens because:','[{"key": "A", "text": "The student is permanently expelled"}, {"key": "B", "text": "It is no longer reinforced"}, {"key": "C", "text": "The student forgets previous learning"}, {"key": "D", "text": "The student is removed from class"}]','B','The correct answer is B. It is no longer reinforced.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','Child and Adolescent Development','medium','''Readiness to learn'' is influenced MOST by:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Jean Piaget''s developmental stages only"}, {"key": "B", "text": "B.F. Skinner''s reinforcement only"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Both maturation and motivation"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Albert Bandura''s modeling only"}]','C','The correct answer is C. Both maturation and motivation.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','Child and Adolescent Development','medium','Which best illustrates ''modeling'' in Bandura''s theory?','[{"key": "A", "text": "A teacher punishes a student for bad behavior"}, {"key": "B", "text": "A student imitates the positive behavior of a teacher they admire"}, {"key": "C", "text": "A student memorizes facts from a textbook"}, {"key": "D", "text": "A student fails a test and is given a lower grade"}]','B','The correct answer is B. A student imitates the positive behavior of a teacher they admire.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','Principles of Teaching','medium','A teacher letting students choose how to demonstrate learning (written, oral, or visual) is applying:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Traditional testing"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Multiple means of expression (Universal Design for Learning)"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Rote memorization"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Standardized assessment"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Multiple means of expression (Universal Design for Learning).','elementary'),
('Professional Education','Principles of Teaching','medium','The lesson plan component that helps students see the ''big picture'' or connect the lesson to their lives is:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Learning Objectives"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Motivation / Hook"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Generalization / Abstraction"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Materials List"}]','C','The correct answer is C. Generalization / Abstraction.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','Principles of Teaching','medium','An educator using formative, summative, AND diagnostic assessment is using:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Single-method assessment"}, {"key": "B", "text": "A triangulated / balanced assessment approach"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Standardized testing only"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Portfolio-only assessment"}]','B','The correct answer is B. A triangulated / balanced assessment approach.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','Principles of Teaching','hard','A characteristic of constructivist teaching is that:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Students passively receive information"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Students actively construct their own understanding through experience"}, {"key": "C", "text": "The teacher is the only knowledge source"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Memorization is the primary strategy"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Students actively construct their own understanding through experience.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','Principles of Teaching','hard','''Debriefing'' after a role-play activity is important because it:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Gives the teacher time to rest"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Helps students process, reflect on the experience, and draw lessons"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Grades the performance"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Formally ends the activity"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Helps students process, reflect on the experience, and draw lessons.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','Principles of Teaching','hard','Heterogeneous grouping means:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Grouping students by ability level"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Mixing students of different abilities, backgrounds, and skills in one group"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Grouping students by gender"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Grouping by academic performance"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Mixing students of different abilities, backgrounds, and skills in one group.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','Principles of Teaching','hard','A curriculum map provides:','[{"key": "A", "text": "A map showing where the school is located"}, {"key": "B", "text": "A visual overview of what is taught, when, and how it aligns with standards"}, {"key": "C", "text": "A list of field trip routes"}, {"key": "D", "text": "A list of all textbooks used"}]','B','The correct answer is B. A visual overview of what is taught, when, and how it aligns with standards.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','The Teaching Profession','hard','A newly hired teacher should FIRST:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Redesign the entire curriculum"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Familiarize themselves with school policies, culture, and student needs"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Replace the previous teacher''s methods entirely"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Assign seats and rules without student input"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Familiarize themselves with school policies, culture, and student needs.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','The Teaching Profession','hard','Teacher salary adjustments are governed by the:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Salary Standardization Law (SSL), updated by Congress"}, {"key": "B", "text": "RA 7836"}, {"key": "C", "text": "RA 9155"}, {"key": "D", "text": "RA 4670 exclusively"}]','A','The correct answer is A. Salary Standardization Law (SSL), updated by Congress.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','The Teaching Profession','hard','A teacher campaigning for a political candidate on school grounds violates:','[{"key": "A", "text": "No rule \u2014 teachers are free to campaign"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Election laws and DepEd regulations on political neutrality in schools"}, {"key": "C", "text": "RA 4670"}, {"key": "D", "text": "RA 7836"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Election laws and DepEd regulations on political neutrality in schools.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','The Teaching Profession','hard','''Professional jealousy'' among colleagues is BEST addressed by:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Avoiding all interaction with jealous colleagues"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Practicing professionalism, collaboration, and reporting if it escalates"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Retaliating"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Working alone always"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Practicing professionalism, collaboration, and reporting if it escalates.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','The Teaching Profession','hard','Under RA 4670, teachers have the right to:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Assign unlimited homework"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Organize and join professional organizations"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Fail all misbehaving students"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Refuse classroom observations"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Organize and join professional organizations.','elementary'),
('Professional Education','The Teaching Profession','hard','The ''Positive Discipline'' approach focuses on:','[{"key": "A", "text": "Fear and punishment"}, {"key": "B", "text": "Developing self-discipline, responsibility, and mutual respect"}, {"key": "C", "text": "Strict compliance to all rules"}, {"key": "D", "text": "Rewarding only the top students"}]','B','The correct answer is B. Developing self-discipline, responsibility, and mutual respect.','elementary');
